msgstr "Dispela em mak bilong ol hap bilong ol lain i stap long ol hap bilong ol paragraf."

#: temp.glade:18082
msgid "Base Line\n"
"Spacing (pt):"
msgstr "Base Line Spacing (pt):"

#: temp.glade:18104
msgid "Align Text to Baseline - uses fixed line spacing"
msgstr ""

#: temp.glade:18107
msgid "For high quality typesetting it is\n"
"best practice to Align the Text\n"
"to the Baseline (i.e. on grid). This\n"
"ensures consistent line spacing\n"
"and front-to-back registration.\n\n"
"Note that this may leave larger\n"
"empty spaces at the end of pages\n"
"which will need to be manually\n"
"adjusted using the Adjust List."
msgstr ""

#: temp.glade:18117
msgid "Align Text to Baseline"
msgstr ""

#: temp.glade:18127
msgid "Align Text to Baseline Grid (On-Grid/Off-Grid)"
msgstr "Stretim ol tok long Grid bilong Baseline (On-Grid/Off-Grid)"

#: temp.glade:18130
msgid "For high quality typesetting it is\n"
"best practice to Align the Text\n"
"to the (baseline) Grid. This\n"
"ensures consistent line spacing\n"
"and front-to-back registration.\n\n"
"However, for quick draft printouts\n"
"or typesetting for thicker paper,\n"
"Variable Line Spacing mode enables\n"
"vertical justification which fills \n"
"each column of text as needed to\n"
"use up the entire page.\n\n"
"Warning: This is a major 'mode' change.\n"
"Everything will shift as a result. Consider\n"
"carefully before changing this setting."
msgstr "Long ol kain kain pepa, ol i save yusim ol kain"

#: temp.glade:18158
msgid "Variable Line Spacing - to vertically justify columns of text"
msgstr ""

#: temp.glade:18161
msgid "Allowing a small increase in the (vertical)\n"
"line spacing allows the text to stretch \n"
"vertically to fill the entire column.\n\n"
"This will also enable 'Fill Columns', but you \n"
"can turn that off to see how much extra\n"
"space there is at the end of each column.\n\n"
"Warning: This will cause major changes to\n"
"the layout of the entire document. It will \n"
"also place headings exactly rather than \n"
"rounding to the nearest number of lines.\n\n"
"Do NOT use this setting if doing final\n"
"typesetting for thin Bible paper as \n"
"front-to-back registration is not\n"
"enforced with Variable Line Spacing."
msgstr "Sapos yu larim liklik hap bilong ol lain i stap namel long ol lain i go antap, dispela bai opim rot long ol rait i ken go antap long ol lain i stap long hap bilong en na pulapim olgeta lain. Dispela bai opim rot long 'Putim Ol Kolon', tasol yu ken pasim rot bilong lukim hamas hap i stap long pinis bilong olgeta lain. Tok lukaut: Dispela bai mekim bikpela senis long pasin bilong putim ol lain i stap insait long pepa. NO ken yusim dispela pasin sapos yu no yusim dispela pasin long raitim ol tok long pepa bilong Baibel."

#: temp.glade:18179
msgid "Variable Line Spacing"
msgstr "Ol i save senisim mak bilong ol lain i stap namel long ol lain i stap long rot"

#: temp.glade:18189
msgid "Fill Columns"
msgstr "Putim Ol Kolom"

#: temp.glade:18190
msgid "Variable/Increased Line Spacing"
msgstr "Ol lain i save senisim/planim ol lain i gat bikpela mak"

#: temp.glade:18194
msgid "A small increase in the (vertical)\n"
"line spacing allows the text to\n"
"stretch to fill the entire column.\n\n"
"This is called vertical justification\n"
"and is useful for Draft Printouts\n"
"where the page can be filled\n"
"without manual intervention to \n"
"eliminate unwanted gaps at the \n"
"end of columns. The setting \n"
"'Allow Unbalanced Columns' \n"
"automatically gets enabled when\n"
"you choose this setting."
msgstr "Dispela i makim olsem ol i mas putim ol liklik hap bilong ol rait i stap namel long ol lain i stap long hap bilong rait. Dispela i makim olsem ol i mas putim ol liklik hap bilong ol rait i stap namel long ol lain i stap long hap bilong rait."

#: temp.glade:18242
msgid "Notelines"
msgstr "Ol tok bilong en"

#: temp.glade:18246
msgid "Include ruled margins to provide space\n"
"for personal notes, reflections, and artwork.\n"
"Typically called 'Journaling Bibles' or 'Wide-\n"
"Margin Bibles'.\n\n"
"Hint: Set the Binding Gutter to a larger value\n"
"(>40mm) and enable Outer Gutter. Other\n"
"settings to control the appearance and spacing\n"
"of the Notelines are in the 'Page Layout and\n"
"Spacing' section of the Advanced > Other tab."
msgstr "Sampela hap bilong pes i gat ol mak bilong en. Ol i kolim ol dispela mak olsem 'Journaling Bibles' o 'Wide-Margin Bibles.'"

#: temp.glade:18273
msgid "Set the color of the Notelines."
msgstr "Makim kala bilong ol Notel."

#: temp.glade:18286
msgid "Mirror Pages"
msgstr "Ol Pes i Gat Ol Samting i Kamap"

#: temp.glade:18287
msgid "Mirror page layout"
msgstr "Ol pes i stap long pes"

#: temp.glade:18291
msgid "Mirror Pages makes use of an Inner+Outer layout.\n"
"This will make the left page header the inner header and\n"
"the right page header will be shown on the outer edge\n"
"(i.e. headers on odd and even pages are mirrored).\n\n"
"Behaviour for Diglots:\n"
"Note that when creating a Diglot, this will place the\n"
"primary text as the Inner text (closest to the spine),\n"
"and the secondary text as the Outer text (closest to\n"
"the edge of the page).\n\n"
"If you always want the Primary text on the left and\n"
"Secondary text on the right regardless of whether\n"
"it is an odd or even page, then turn off this option."
msgstr "Ol pes bilong ol pes i gat ol liklik hap bilong ol i stap long en, na ol pes i stap long hap saut i stap long en. Ol pes i gat ol liklik hap bilong ol i stap long en. Sapos yu laik lukim ol tok long pes i stap long han kais na ol tok long pes i stap long han sut, maski pes i no stret o i no stret, orait pasim dispela opsen."

#: temp.glade:18324
msgid "Page Setup"
msgstr "Painim pes"

#: temp.glade:18360
msgid "Gutter width for two column layout"
msgstr "Wasting bilong gutter bilong tupela kolon"

#: temp.glade:18363 temp.glade:24869
msgid "This is the space between \n"
"the text of the two columns \n"
"(measured in millimeters)."
msgstr "Dispela em mak bilong mak bilong ol hap bilong ol dispela tupela kolon (ol i makim long millimeta)."

#: temp.glade:18387
msgid "Adjust top of vertical rule"
msgstr "Stretim het bilong vertikal lo"

#: temp.glade:18390 temp.glade:18447
msgid "This setting raises (using a negative value) or \n"
"lowers (using a positive value) the starting \n"
"point of the vertical rule between columns.\n"
"(Value in pts)."
msgstr "Dispela mak i save mekim namba bilong ol lain i stap namel long ol pos i go antap (long namba i no stret) o i go daun (long namba i stret). (Value in pts)."

#: temp.glade:18422 temp.glade:24894
msgid "This is the space (mm) between \n"
"the text of the two columns."
msgstr "Dispela em ples (mm) namel long ol dispela tupela kolon."

#: temp.glade:18427 temp.glade:24899
msgid "Gutter \n"
"Width (mm):"
msgstr "Wasting:"

#: temp.glade:18452 temp.glade:25027
msgid "Adjust\n"
"Top (pt):"
msgstr "Stretim het (pt):"

#: temp.glade:18465
msgid "Rule (line) Thickness"
msgstr "Raun (lain) Mak bilong en"

#: temp.glade:18468 temp.glade:18560
msgid "This sets the thickness (pt) of rules (lines)\n"
"in the document. This includes the\n"
"horizontal rule between the header\n"
"and the text, the vertical column gutter\n"
"rule and the study notes inter-column rule."
msgstr "Dispela i makim mak bilong ol lo (lain) long pepa, olsem ol lo i stap namel long het tok na ol lo i stap namel long ol lo i stap long ol het tok, ol lo i stap namel long ol lo i stap long ol kolon, na ol lo i stap namel long ol kolon bilong ol not bilong stadi."

#: temp.glade:18493 temp.glade:18494 temp.glade:24999
msgid "Vertical Rule in Gutter"
msgstr "Stretpela Lo Long Gutter"

#: temp.glade:18498 temp.glade:25004
msgid "Check this option to include a center\n"
"line between the two columns."
msgstr "Makim dispela opsen bilong putim wanpela namel lain namel long tupela kolom."

#: temp.glade:18517 temp.glade:18518
msgid "Allow Unbalanced Columns"
msgstr "Larim ol Kolon i No Stap Gut"

#: temp.glade:18522
msgid "Check this option to allow a different\n"
"number of lines in each column. This\n"
"is especially important when using\n"
"Variable Line Spacing mode and\n"
"you are trying to Fill Columns.\n\n"
"To alter the maximum number of\n"
"Unbalanced Lines at the end of a\n"
"page, visit the Advanced page,\n"
"select the Other tab, and expand\n"
"the Page Layout and Spacing section.\n\n"
"If this setting is highlighted in orange\n"
"it means that the abovementioned\n"
"setting was set to 0 (rendering this\n"
"setting inactive), and has now been\n"
"increased to the default value of 3."
msgstr "Lukim dispela opesen bilong larim narapela lain lain i stap long wan wan kolon. Dispela i bikpela samting taim yu yusim Variable Line Spacing mode na yu laik Filling Columns. Bilong senisim namba bilong ol lain i no gat gutpela skel long pinis bilong pes, go long Advanced pes, makim narapela tab, na opim bikpela hap bilong Page Layout na Spacing. Sapos dispela mak i stap long orens, dispela i makim olsem mak i stap long namba 0 (ol i no mekim wok long en), na nau mak i go antap inap long namba 3"

#: temp.glade:18566
msgid "Thickness\n"
"of Rule (pt):"
msgstr "Mak bilong ol mak"

#: temp.glade:18598
msgid "One or two column layout"
msgstr "Ol i putim wanpela o tupela kolon"

#: temp.glade:18602
msgid "If this setting is checked on, but\n"
"inactive, it is due to Diglot being\n"
"active (which obviously must use \n"
"the Two Column layout).\n\n"
"If you get an unexpected result, check\n"
"the \"Use One/Two Column Layout ...\"\n"
"setting near the end of the Body tab\n"
"which is only accessible when using\n"
"the Full View mode."
msgstr "Sapos yu makim dispela mak, tasol yu no mekim wok, dispela i kamap long wanem, Diglot i wok (olsem na yu mas yusim tupela kolumet). Sapos yu kisim wanpela samting yu no bin ting bai kamap, orait skelim mak \"Use One/Two Columet Layout ...\" klostu long pinis bilong bodi tab em yu inap lukim tasol taim yu yusim full view mode."

#: temp.glade:18668
msgid "Header spacing"
msgstr "Hap bilong het tok"

#: temp.glade:18671
msgid "This setting determines the vertical positioning\n"
"of the header line by setting the amount of space\n"
"between the header and the top of the text. (pts)\n\n"
"The top of the main text area is 1 base line spacing \n"
"above the base line of the first line of the body text."
msgstr "Dispela sait i makim olsem wanem het rait bai stap antap long het rait na hap bilong het rait i stap antap long hap bilong het rait. (pts) Long hap antap bilong hap bilong het rait, wanpela hap bilong ol hap bilong het rait i stap antap long hap bilong namba wan hap bilong het rait."

#: temp.glade:18704
msgid "Footer position"
msgstr "Ples bilong lek"

#: temp.glade:18707
msgid "This setting can be used to increase/decrease the \n"
"space between the end of the text and the footer line."
msgstr "Dispela sait inap helpim yu long mekim hap hap i stap namel long pinis bilong teks na hap hap i stap daunbilo bilong pes i go bikpela o liklik."

#: temp.glade:18736
msgid "Bottom margin"
msgstr "Ples daunbilo"

#: temp.glade:18739 temp.glade:19563
msgid "The distance (mm) from the bottom of the \n"
"main text area to the bottom of the page.\n\n"
"The bottom of the main text area is calculated\n"
"from the descender of the final line of text \n"
"(including any footnotes)."
msgstr "Long hap daunbilo bilong hap bilong bikpela rait i go daun long hap daunbilo bilong pes."

#: temp.glade:18773
msgid "Side margin width"
msgstr "Wastem bilong sait"

#: temp.glade:18776 temp.glade:19397
msgid "The distance (mm) from the \n"
"edge of the page to the start\n"
"of the text area. Note that the\n"
"left and right (or inner and \n"
"outer) margins are set to be\n"
"identical. If you require a \n"
"greater inner margin, then\n"
"set the Binding Gutter above."
msgstr "Long hapsait bilong pes (mm) i go inap long hap bilong rait. Tingim olsem sait long han kais na han sut (o insait na ausait) i wankain. Sapos yu laik gat bikpela hapsait moa, orait putim Binding Gutter antap."

#: temp.glade:18791
msgid "0.0"
msgstr ""

#: temp.glade:18811
msgid "Space between horizontal rule and main text area"
msgstr "Hap namel long ol lo i stap long hap daunbilo na hap bilong ol bikpela tok"

#: temp.glade:18814 temp.glade:19501
msgid "The space (pt) between the horizontal rule\n"
"and the top of the main text area. Note that\n"
"the first line actually starts a little bit below\n"
"where the the main text area starts.\n\n"
"The top of the main text area is 1 base line spacing \n"
"above the base line of the first line of the body text."
msgstr "Dispela hap (pt) namel long horizontal rule na het bilong main text area. Tingim olsem namba wan lain i stat liklik aninit long hap we main text area i stat. Het bilong main text area i stap 1 base line spacing antap long base line bilong namba wan lain bilong body text."

#: temp.glade:18848
msgid "Top margin"
msgstr "Namba bilong ol samting i no gat pe"

#: temp.glade:18851 temp.glade:19433
msgid "The distance (mm) from the top of the page\n"
"to the top of the main text area. Note that\n"
"the first line actually starts a little bit below\n"
"where the the main text area starts.\n\n"
"The top of the main text area is 1 base line spacing \n"
"above the base line of the first line of the body text."
msgstr "Dispela mak i makim mak bilong mak bilong ol hap bilong ol pes i stap long hap antap long pes na i go long hap antap long hap bilong ol bikpela rait."

#: temp.glade:18886
msgid "Tweak top margin (auto adjust)"
msgstr "Painim mak bilong hap antap (setim aut)"

#: temp.glade:18890
msgid "Fine Tune Top Margin:\n\n"
"This button is only active when PTXprint has a suggestion to\n"
"shrink or expand the top margin slightly to minimise wasted \n"
"vertical space on the page. Click to accept the suggestion.\n\n"
"If there is more than half a line of 'spare' space on the \n"
"page then the top margin will decrease slightly to\n"
"fit one more line of text on the page.\n\n"
"If there is less than half a line of 'spare' space on the \n"
"page then the top margin will increase slightly to \n"
"fill the page more evenly (with the same number of \n"
"lines of text).\n\n"
"If you prefer to keep the exact top margin specified, \n"
"then do NOT click this option. Instead, use the similar\n"
"button to adjust either the Line Spacing or Bottom Margin."
msgstr "Fine Tune Top Margin: Dispela boten i save wok taim PTXprint i gat wanpela tok long liklik o opim liklik liklik hap bilong hap antap bilong liklik hap bilong sait. Klik long orait long tok. Sapos i gat moa long hap hap bilong hap i stap long pes, orait hap antap bai go daun liklik bilong inapim wanpela hap moa bilong rait long pes. Sapos i gat liklik hap hap tasol bilong pes, orait hap antap bai kamap bikpela liklik na bai pes i pulap gut (ol wankain hap bilong pes). Sapos yu laik holim wankain hap antap, no ken klik long dispela opsen."

#: temp.glade:18921
msgid "Tweak bottom margin (auto adjust)"
msgstr "Painim liklik hap daunbilo bilong pes (setim aut)"

#: temp.glade:18925
msgid "Fine Tune Bottom Margin:\n\n"
"This button is only active when PTXprint has a suggestion to\n"
"shrink or expand the bottom margin slightly to minimise wasted \n"
"vertical space on the page. Click to accept the suggestion.\n\n"
"If there is more than half a line of 'spare' space on the \n"
"page then the bottom margin will decrease slightly to\n"
"fit one more line of text on the page.\n\n"
"If there is less than half a line of 'spare' space on the \n"
"page then the bottom margin will increase slightly to \n"
"fill the page more evenly (with the same number of \n"
"lines of text).\n\n"
"If you prefer to keep the exact bottom margin specified, \n"
"then do NOT click this option. Instead, use the similar\n"
"button to adjust either the Line Spacing or Top Margin."
msgstr "Fine Tune Bottom Margin: Dispela boten i save wok taim PTXprint i gat wanpela toksave long liklik o opim liklik liklik daunbilo hap bilong liklik hap bilong sait. Klik long orait long toksave. Sapos i gat moa long hap bilong sait, orait daunbilo hap bai go daun liklik bilong inapim wanpela lain moa bilong rait long pes. Sapos i gat liklik hap hap tasol bilong pes, orait daunbilo hap bilong pes bai kamap bikpela liklik na bai pes i pulap gut (ol wankain hap bilong pes). Sapos yu laik holim stret hap bilong pes, orait no ken klik long dispela opsen."

#: temp.glade:19268
msgid "Place Footer Text Above the Bottom Margin"
msgstr "Putim Footer Tekst antap long Bottom Margin"

#: temp.glade:19269
msgid "Don't place footer in the margin area"
msgstr "No ken putim footer long hap i stap klostu long mak"

#: temp.glade:19273
msgid "Normally the footer page number sits\n"
"in the bottom margin. \n\n"
"However if you need  the page number to\n"
"be placed above the bottom margin (where\n"
"the text would normally flow until) then \n"
"enable this option."
msgstr "Planti taim namba bilong pes long hap daunbilo i stap long hap daunbilo. Tasol sapos yu laik bai namba bilong pes i stap antap long hap daunbilo (we ol tok bai i go inap long) orait opisim dispela opsen."

#: temp.glade:19303
msgid "The distance (mm) from the edge of the page\n"
"to the bottom of the footer area."
msgstr "Long hap bilong sait (mm) i go long hap daunbilo bilong pes daunbilo."

#: temp.glade:19308 temp.glade:19372
msgid "8.5mm"
msgstr "8.5 milim"

#: temp.glade:19323 temp.glade:19324
msgid "Horizontal Rule"
msgstr "Lo Bilong Ol Hap"

#: temp.glade:19328
msgid "Check this option to add a horizontal\n"
"line under the page header, before the\n"
"main body text begins."
msgstr "Makim dispela opsen bilong putim wanpela lain long hap daunbilo bilong het pes bilong pes, paslain long ol bikpela hap bilong pes i kirap."

#: temp.glade:19347 temp.glade:31047 temp.glade:31060
msgid " "
msgstr ""

#: temp.glade:19365
msgid "The distance (mm) from the top of the page\n"
"to the top of the header area. Note that due to \n"
"the ascent of the font, the header text actually \n"
"starts a little bit below the top of the header area."
msgstr "Dispela mak i makim mak bilong hap bilong pes i stap long het bilong pes."

#: temp.glade:19408
msgid "Side Margin\n"
"Width (mm):"
msgstr "Long Side Margin Width (mm):"

#: temp.glade:19442
msgid "Start of Page to\n"
"Top of Text (mm):"
msgstr "Stat bilong pes i go long het bilong rait (mm):"

#: temp.glade:19467
msgid "The space (pt) between the bottom of the header\n"
"and the top of the main text area. Note that\n"
"the first line actually starts a little bit below\n"
"where the the main text area starts.\n\n"
"The top of the main text area is 1 base line spacing \n"
"above the base line of the first line of the body text."
msgstr "Dispela hap hap (pt) namel long hap daunbilo bilong het na hap antap bilong main teks eria. Tingim olsem namba wan lain i stat liklik aninit long hap we main teks eria i stat."

#: temp.glade:19476
msgid "Bottom of Header\n"
"to Top of Text (pt):"
msgstr "Long hap daunbilo bilong het tok i go long hap antap bilong tok (pt):"

#: temp.glade:19510
msgid "Space between Rule\n"
"and Top of Text (pt):"
msgstr "Hap namel long Rule na Top of Text (pt):"

#: temp.glade:19532
msgid "Footer position - space between text and footer"
msgstr "Ples bilong footer - hap namel long rait na footer"

#: temp.glade:19535
msgid "The distance (pt) from the bottom of the text area\n"
"to the TOP of the footer (including ascenders)."
msgstr "Long hap daunbilo bilong hap bilong rait i go long hap antap bilong hap daunbilo (na ol hap i go antap tu)."

#: temp.glade:19539
msgid "Bottom of Text to\n"
"Top of Footer (pt):"
msgstr "Long hap daunbilo bilong rait i go long hap antap bilong pes (pt):"

#: temp.glade:19572
msgid "Bottom of Text to\n"
"End of Page (mm):"
msgstr "Long hap daunbilo bilong rait i go long hap daunbilo bilong pes (mm):"

#: temp.glade:19596
msgid "Margins"
msgstr "Ol mak"

#: temp.glade:19616
msgid "Page Setup, Font Size and Line Spacing. \n"
"Margins, Columns and Rules (lines)."
msgstr "Ol pes i gat ol mak bilong en, bikpela fon na mak bilong ol lain i stap namel long ol lain."

#: temp.glade:19676
msgid "Bold:"
msgstr "Toktok i gat bikpela mak:"

#: temp.glade:19688
msgid "Italic:"
msgstr "Tok i stap long rot:"

#: temp.glade:19700
msgid "Bold Italic:"
msgstr "Tok i stap long pes:"

#: temp.glade:19713
msgid "Body Text\n"
"(Regular):"
msgstr "Tok bilong bodi (tokples nating):"

#: temp.glade:19723 temp.glade:19746 temp.glade:19766 temp.glade:19786
#: temp.glade:19985 temp.glade:32608
msgid "Select Font..."
msgstr "Makim Font..."

#: temp.glade:19724
msgid "Select Regular font"
msgstr "Makim Font"

#: temp.glade:19729
msgid "Click to select the main font for the publication.\n"
"Note that the font chooser dialog also has a\n"
"number of other options for setting advanced\n"
"font features and, if needed, Graphite rendering."
msgstr "Klik long fon bilong makim nambawan fon bilong dispela nius. Tingim olsem fon bilong makim fon i gat sampela narapela opsen bilong putim ol fon samting na sapos yu nidim, Graphite."

#: temp.glade:19747
msgid "Select Bold font"
msgstr "Makim Bold"

#: temp.glade:19752
msgid "If you see the style in parentheses (bold)\n"
"this indicates that PTXprint could not\n"
"locate the bold style and will fake the style."
msgstr "Sapos yu lukim stil insait long parentesis (bol) dispela i makim olsem PTXprint i no inap painim stil long bol na bai giamanim stil."

#: temp.glade:19767
msgid "Select Italic font"
msgstr "Makim ol hap tok"

#: temp.glade:19772
msgid "If you see the style in parentheses (italic)\n"
"this indicates that PTXprint could not\n"
"locate the italic style and will fake the style."
msgstr "Sapos yu lukim stil insait long parentesis (italik) dispela i makim olsem PTXprint i no inap painim stil i stap long italik na bai giamanim stil."

#: temp.glade:19787
msgid "Select Bold Italic font"
msgstr "Makim Bold Italic fon"

#: temp.glade:19792
msgid "If you see either of the styles in parentheses (bold)\n"
"or (italic) this indicates that PTXprint could not\n"
"locate the style and will fake the bold-italic style."
msgstr "Sapos yu lukim wanpela bilong ol stils insait long parentesis (bolot) o (bolot) dispela i makim olsem PTXprint i no inap painim stils na bai giamanim stils long bolot-bolot."

#: temp.glade:19806
msgid "Refresh Font List button"
msgstr "Rausim Fonts List"

#: temp.glade:19810
msgid "Refresh Font List:\n"
"If you have recently installed a font but it\n"
"doesn't show in the font list, then try\n"
"clicking this button to refresh the list.\n\n"
"If it still doesn't show up, then try re-installing\n"
"the font (in Windows, locate the font file, then\n"
"right-click on it and select \"Install For All Users\").\n\n"
"And remember to Refresh the Font List again."
msgstr "Refresh Font List: Sapos yu bin putim nupela fon tasol em i no stap yet long fon list, orait traim long klikim dispela boton bilong refresh list. Sapos em i no stap yet, orait traim long putim gen fon (long Windows, painim fon file, na klik long en na makim \"Install For All Users\")."

#: temp.glade:19840 temp.glade:19841
msgid "Enable Colored Text (as Specified in Stylesheet)"
msgstr "Toktok long ol kala (olsem ol i makim long Stylesheet)"

#: temp.glade:19845
msgid "The marker specifications in stylesheets also\n"
"include the \\Color parameter. If this option\n"
"is checked, then these settings will be used\n"
"to produce colored text output. For example\n"
"the \\wj Words of Jesus\\wj* marker might\n"
"specify \\Color Red which will only take effect\n"
"if this option is also enabled - otherwise all\n"
"text will appear in black."
msgstr "Ol maker long stylesheets i gat tu dispela parameta \\Color. Sapos yu makim dispela opsen, orait ol bai yusim dispela ol maker long kamapim ol tok bilong ol i gat kala. Olsem: tok bilong Jisas long tok bilong Jisas i gat kala."

#: temp.glade:19873
msgid "To change the script for numbers, click here\n"
"to locate the Digit Mapping setting at the end\n"
"of the Font selection dialog."
msgstr "Bilong senisim skrip bilong ol namba, klik hia long painim Digit Mapping setting long pinis bilong fon seleksen dialog."

#: temp.glade:19904
msgid "Font Configuration"
msgstr "Ol fon i stap olsem wanem"

#: temp.glade:19936
msgid "Find Missing\n"
"Characters:"
msgstr "Painim Ol Karakter i No Stap Long Tok Pisin:"

#: temp.glade:19938
msgid "Find Missing Characters button"
msgstr "Painim Ol Karakter i Misim"

#: temp.glade:19942
msgid "If the primary font is missing any characters\n"
"(special punctuation, quotes or glossary markers), \n"
"then these can be listed here, and handled using\n"
"the Font specified below.\n\n"
"It is recommended that you select as many\n"
"scripture books as available before using\n"
"this tool to find missing characters.\n\n"
"Note that the following characters are reserved\n"
"and are ignored by the Fallback font functionality:\n"
"           \\u2018 \\u2019 \\u201c \\u201d * # %"
msgstr "Sapos i no gat sampela mak (ol mak bilong putim mak, ol tok piksa o ol mak bilong ol tok i stap long ol tok bilong en), yu ken raitim nem bilong ol dispela mak long hia, na yusim dispela fon i stap daunbilo."

#: temp.glade:19966
msgid "Select a font to be used as a substitute or\n"
"\"fallback\" for the characters listed above\n"
"which are not in the Regular font.\n\n"
"Note that if the label text is RED, it means \n"
"that the font currently selected doesn't \n"
"have all the missing characters either, \n"
"so it is wise to choose another font."
msgstr "Makim wanpela fon we bai stap olsem senis o \"fallback\" bilong ol karakta i stap long lista antap, em ol i no stap long fon bilong Redi."

#: temp.glade:19975
msgid "Font to Display any\n"
"Missing Characters:"
msgstr "Font bilong soim ol mak i lus:"

#: temp.glade:19986
msgid "Select font to display missing characters"
msgstr "Makim fon bilong soim ol mak i lus"

#: temp.glade:19990
msgid "Click to select a font to be used as a substitute\n"
"or \"fallback\" for the characters listed above\n"
"which are not in the Regular font."
msgstr "Klik long fon bilong makim wanpela fon yu laik yusim olsem senis o \"fallback\" bilong ol dispela mak i stap antap, em ol i no stap long fon bilong Olpela fon."

#: temp.glade:20002
msgid "Missing Characters"
msgstr "Ol Karakter i No Stap Long Baibel"

#: temp.glade:20005
msgid "First use the button (on the left) to find\n"
"any characters missing from the primary\n"
"font. You may add to this list if needed.\n"
"Use spaces between items.\n"
"Note that you can also use \\u0ABC codes\n"
"to enter hard-to-type characters."
msgstr "Pastaim yusim dispela boten (long han kais) long painim ol karakta i lus long fon bilong namba wan hap. Yu ken putim sampela hap long dispela lista sapos yu nidim. Yusim ol hap namel long ol atikol. Tingim olsem yu ken yusim tu ol kod bilong \\u0ABC long putim ol karakta i hatwok long taipim."

#: temp.glade:20030 temp.glade:20031
msgid "Use Fallback Font"
msgstr "Yusim Fonts"

#: temp.glade:20035
msgid "This setting is used to prevent \"tofu\" boxes [] in \n"
"the printed text. If the primary font is missing any\n"
"special characters (for example curly quotes),\n"
"then an alternative \"fallback\" font can be used\n"
"to ensure that they are displayed properly."
msgstr "Sapos i no gat sampela mak bilong ol dispela hap tok (olsem ol krol komet), orait yu ken yusim narapela hap tok bilong \"fallback\" bilong soim ol dispela hap tok stret."

#: temp.glade:20082 temp.glade:20083
msgid "Hyphenate"
msgstr "Ol i bin wokim ol liklik hap ston"

#: temp.glade:20087
msgid "To hyphenate properly you need to first create a \n"
"Hyphenation List using the button on the left.\n"
"This will create a XeTeX hyphenation list from the\n"
"hyphenation list in Paratext.\n\n"
"Note that for Hyphenation to work properly, the\n"
"Spacing Adjustments 'Between Letters' option needs \n"
"to be disabled."
msgstr ""

#: temp.glade:20107
msgid "Import List..."
msgstr "Ol i mas kisim ol samting bilong ol i kam long narapela kantri."

#: temp.glade:20108
msgid "Create Hyphenation List"
msgstr "Mekim wanpela lain lain"

#: temp.glade:20112
msgid "Click this button to generate a hyphenation \n"
"list that can be used by XeTeX to optimize\n"
"hyphenation. This will read Paratext's\n"
"HyphenatedWords.txt list and create a\n"
"TeX hyphen list for this language."
msgstr "Klik long dispela boton bilong kamapim wanpela lista bilong ol hap tok i stap namel long tupela hap tok, em XeTeX inap yusim bilong mekim gut ol hap tok. Dispela bai ritim lista bilong Paratext bilong ol hap tok i stap namel long tupela hap tok na wokim wanpela lista bilong ol hap tok bilong dispela tokples."

#: temp.glade:20130
msgid "Omit '-'Hyphen"
msgstr "Lusim hap tok \"-\""

#: temp.glade:20131
msgid "Omit hyphen from hyphenated words"
msgstr "Lusim hap hap tok i stap namel long ol tok i gat hap tok"

#: temp.glade:20135
msgid "Some scripts use hyphenation to break long\n"
"words onto the next line, BUT don't need to\n"
"display the actual '-' character. If this option\n"
"is checked, then \"hyphens\" will be invisible."
msgstr "Sampela skrip i save yusim hap tok bilong brukim ol longpela tok i go long narapela lain, tasol i no gat wok long soim dispela '-' karakta. Sapos yu makim dispela hap tok, orait \"hap tok\" bai i no inap kamap."

#: temp.glade:20150 temp.glade:20151
msgid "Make Hyphens Non-Breaking"
msgstr "Mekim Ol Hap Bilong Tok i No Pinis"

#: temp.glade:20155
msgid "Enable this option to ensure that word-medial hyphens\n"
"within the text never break across two lines.\n\n"
"By default, word-\n"
"medial may break\n"
"across two lines.\n\n"
"If enabled, word-medial will\n"
"always stay on the same line."
msgstr "Sapos yu larim dispela opsen long kamap, bai ol hap tok i stap namel long tupela lain i no ken bruk. Sapos yu larim dispela opsen, ol hap tok i stap namel long tupela lain bai stap long wankain lain."

#: temp.glade:20184
msgid "Hyphenation"
msgstr "Tok i stap namel long tupela hap"

#: temp.glade:20228
msgid "Between Words"
msgstr "Tok i stap namel long tupela tok"

#: temp.glade:20229
msgid "Spacing Between Words"
msgstr "Ol Tok i No Mas Stap Long Hap"

#: temp.glade:20233
msgid "The horizontal distance that the space\n"
"character can use between words is\n"
"adjustable - and allows a greater degree\n"
"of flexibility when trying to shrink or\n"
"grow paragrahs when balancing pages."
msgstr "Ol inap stretim hap mak bilong ol hap i stap namel long ol tok - na dispela inap mekim ol i no ken pret taim ol i wok long daunim o mekim ol paragraf i kamap bikpela taim ol i wok long stretim ol pes."

#: temp.glade:20252
msgid "Between Letters"
msgstr "Ol Gutnius i Stap namel long tupela"

#: temp.glade:20253
msgid "Spacing Between Letters"
msgstr "Ol Tok i Stap namel long Ol Tok"

#: temp.glade:20257
msgid "Enabling letter spacing allows the spaces between\n"
"characters to be adjusted (usually by a very small\n"
"percentage). This might help alleviate space problems.\n"
"Values are in percentage of the text point size and \n"
"get used everywhere. \n\n"
"Warning: Only use this if really needed!\n"
"In some cases, enabling this setting will prevent\n"
"hyphenation from working at all. In other cases it \n"
"can make the text look very ugly.\n\n"
"Note that if this option is disabled, then it is due to\n"
"the Interlinear option being set on the Advanced page.\n"
"These two settings are mutually exclusive."
msgstr "Taim yu larim ol leta i stap namel long ol narapela leta, yu inap senisim hap hap i stap namel long ol dispela leta (olsem liklik hap). Dispela inap helpim yu long daunim ol hevi bilong hap. Ol namba i stap long hap bilong ol bikpela hap bilong ol dispela leta na yu ken yusim long olgeta hap. Tingim olsem sapos dispela opesen i no stap, dispela i kamap long rot bilong Interlinear opesen i stap long Advanced pes."

#: temp.glade:20284
msgid "Spacing Between Words (Min/Shrink)"
msgstr "Hap Mak i Stap namel long ol tok (Min/Shrink)"

#: temp.glade:20288
msgid "When justifying paragraphs, and especially when\n"
"trying to shrink or grow a paragraph to take fewer\n"
"or more lines, the horizontal distance that a space\n"
"uses can be adjusted - allowing the text to shrink\n"
"or grow. Lower values will enable a 'tighter' text\n"
"and make it more flexible, but keep the readers in\n"
"mind - and their need to distinguish word-breaks\n"
"with ease. This value is a % percentage of a normal\n"
"space width. TeX's default value is 66%."
msgstr "Taim yu skelim ol paragraf, na moa yet taim yu traim long daunim o mekim ol paragraf i go bikpela na i go liklik o i go bikpela moa, yu inap senisim hap mak bilong hap mak i stap namel long ol hap tok."

#: temp.glade:20317
msgid "Spacing Between Words (Max/Stretch)"
msgstr "Hap Hap i stap namel long ol tok (Max/Stretch)"

#: temp.glade:20321
msgid "When justifying paragraphs, and especially when\n"
"trying to shrink or grow a paragraph to take fewer\n"
"or more lines, the horizontal distance that a space\n"
"uses can be adjusted - allowing the text to shrink\n"
"or grow. Larger values will enable a 'looser' text\n"
"and make it more flexible to grow, but be careful\n"
"to avoid 'rivers' or white space in paragraphs.\n"
"This value is a % percentage of a normal\n"
"space width. TeX's default value is 150%."
msgstr "Taim yu stretim ol paragraf, na moa yet taim yu traim long daunim o mekim wanpela paragraf i go bikpela na i gat liklik o planti lain, yu ken stretim hap mak bilong hap hap i stap namel long ol paragraf - na bai ol rait i ken kamap liklik o bikpela."

#: temp.glade:20350
msgid "Spacing Between Letters (Min/Shrink)"
msgstr "Hap i Stap namel long Ol Tok (Min/Shrink)"

#: temp.glade:20353
msgid "Values are in percentage of the text point size."
msgstr ""

#: temp.glade:20369
msgid "Spacing Between Letters (Max/Stretch)"
msgstr "Hap namel long ol leta (Max/Stretch)"

#: temp.glade:20372
msgid "Values are in percentage of the text point size.\n"
msgstr ""

#: temp.glade:20391 temp.glade:20410
msgid "Maximum size % that a space\n"
"can grow to when necessary."
msgstr "Namba bilong ol samting i ken kamap bikpela long en taim ol i mas mekim olsem."

#: temp.glade:20395
msgid "Min/Shrink"
msgstr ""

#: temp.glade:20414
msgid "Max/Stretch"
msgstr ""

#: temp.glade:20449
msgid "Edit Adjust List..."
msgstr "Redim na Stretim Ol Toktok..."

#: temp.glade:20450
msgid "Adjust Layout by Shrinking or Expanding Paragraphs"
msgstr "Senisim Ol Tok Bilong Ol Paragraf"

#: temp.glade:20454
msgid "Click to view or edit the Adj List in the Viewer tab."
msgstr "Klik long lukim o senisim Adj List long Visualizer tab."

#: temp.glade:20466
msgid "A Paragraph Adjust List needs to be in this format:\n"
"MRK 2.7 +1    (i.e. expand the para at Mark 2.7 by one line) \n"
"MRK 3.20 -1   (i.e. shrink the para at Mark 3:20 by one line)\n"
"%MARK 4.14 +1   (ignore this line - treat it as a comment)   \n"
"MRK 5.8 +2    (i.e. expand the para at Mark 5.8 by two lines)\n"
"MRK 6.23 +1[2]  (expand the paragraph AFTER the paragraph \n"
"                              which contains MRK 6.23 e.g. a heading.)\n"
"etc.\n"
"Note that adjusting paragraphs needs to be done right at the\n"
"end when all other settings and picture placements have been \n"
"finalized. Otherwise you may need to re-do it all once again."
msgstr "Ol i mas raitim ol tok olsem: MRK 2.7 +1 (em i olsem, skruim wanpela lain long paragraf long Mak 2.7) MRK 3.20 -1 (em i olsem, skruim wanpela lain liklik long paragraf long Mak 3:20) %MARK 4.14 +1 (no ken tingim dispela lain - tingim olsem wanpela tok) MRK 5.8 +2 (em i olsem, skruim tupela lain long paragraf long Mak 5.8) MRK 6.23 +1[2] (painim sampela hap bilong paragraf bihain long paragraf i gat Mak 6.23 olsem het tok) etc. Tingim: Taim yu pinisim olgeta narapela sait na piksa, orait yu mas stretim ol paragraf, nogat, ating yu mas mekim gen."

#: temp.glade:20478
msgid "Adjust Layout by Shrinking\n"
"or Expanding Paragraphs:"
msgstr "Stretim Ol Tok Bilong Baibel Long Rot Bilong Skim O Mekim Ol Paragraf i Winim:"

#: temp.glade:20502
msgid "Spacing Adjustments"
msgstr "Stretim Hap Hap i Stap namel long Haus"

#: temp.glade:20536 temp.glade:20554
msgid "Select the direction for the text to flow. \n"
"Note that the option for \"Top to Bottom\"\n"
"lays out the vertical lines left to right."
msgstr "Makim rot bilong rait i mas ran i go long en. Lukim olsem rot \"Top to Bottom\" i makim ol lain i sanap long han kais i go long han sut."

#: temp.glade:20540
msgid "Text Flow\n"
"Direction:"
msgstr "Rot bilong rait:"

#: temp.glade:20550
msgid "Text direction (Right-to-left RTL etc)"
msgstr "Rot bilong rait (RTL long han sut i go long han kais, na ol narapela samting)"

#: temp.glade:20576
msgid "Text\n"
"Script:"
msgstr "Toktok Script:"

#: temp.glade:20586
msgid "Text script"
msgstr "Toktok skrip"

#: temp.glade:20590
msgid "PTXprint provides additional typesetting \n"
"functionality for some complex scripts: \n"
"arab, mymr, thai, knda, orya, mlym, taml, telu\n\n"
"In most cases leave this setting as \"Default\"."
msgstr "PTXprint i save givim sampela moa save bilong raitim ol tok long sampela kain skrip: Arabic, mymr, Thai, knda, orya, mlym, taml, telu."

#: temp.glade:20613 temp.glade:20614
msgid "Additional Script Settings..."
msgstr "Ol Narapela Senis Bilong Ol Skripsa..."

#: temp.glade:20619
msgid "A small number of complex scripts (such as\n"
"Burmese & Indic) have additional options\n"
"which can be set individually."
msgstr "Sampela liklik lain bilong ol skripsa i gat planti tok (olsem Tok Burma na Tok India) i gat sampela narapela tok we ol inap putim wan wan."

#: temp.glade:20636
msgid "Complex\n"
"Scripts:"
msgstr "Ol Skripsa i Gat Planti Tok:"

#: temp.glade:20646
msgid "Specify Line\n"
"Break Locale:"
msgstr "Tokim ples bilong hap lain i bruk:"

#: temp.glade:20648
msgid "Enable Line Break Locale"
msgstr "Enable Line Break Locale (Toktok bilong lain i no gat lain)"

#: temp.glade:20652
msgid "Some languages that use complex scripts need\n"
"dictionary support for line breaking. Note that\n"
"the dictionary used will be LWC-specific.\n"
"For example, zh for Chinese, ko for Korean, etc.\n"
"Note that Graphite fonts can also have line breaking\n"
"rules which can be enabled by using the gr locale."
msgstr "Sampela tokples i yusim ol kain kain skrip i mas i gat dikseneri bilong helpim ol long brukim ol lain. Tingim olsem dikseneri ol i yusim bai i stret long LWC. Olsem zh bilong tok Saina, ko bilong tok Korea, etc. Tingim olsem Graphite fon tu inap gat ol lo bilong brukim ol lain em yu ken yusim gr locale."

#: temp.glade:20671
msgid "Set Line Break Locale"
msgstr "Makim lain i bruk"

#: temp.glade:20675
msgid "ja = Japanese\n"
"km = Khmer\n"
"ko = Korean\n"
"my = Myanmar\n"
"th = Thai\n"
"zh = Chinese\n"
"   OR\n"
"gr = Graphite"
msgstr "ja = Japan km = Khmer ko = Korea my = Myanmar th = Thai zh = Saina OR gr = Grafit"

#: temp.glade:20704
msgid "RTL Book\n"
"Binding"
msgstr "RTL Buk Bilong Pasim Ol Buk"

#: temp.glade:20706
msgid "Set the binding to Right (for RTL publications)"
msgstr "Makim binding long Right (long ol RTL nius)"

#: temp.glade:20710
msgid "Enable this for Right-to-Left\n"
"publications (so that the book\n"
"is bound on the right hand side)."
msgstr "Makim dispela long ol buk i stap long han sut i go long han kais (olsem buk i stap long han sut)."

#: temp.glade:20730
msgid "Writing System"
msgstr "Ol Tok Bilong Rait"

#: temp.glade:20763
msgid "Basic Fonts and Advanced Font options.\n"
"Also a range of Advanced typography\n"
"settings to support any Writing System.\n"
"Advanced Spacing Settings. Fallback fonts\n"
"for characters missing in primary font."
msgstr "Ol fon bilong ol fon i no gat nem."

#: temp.glade:20815
msgid "Book Introductions"
msgstr "Ol Tok Bilong Kirap Long Buk"

#: temp.glade:20816
msgid "Enable book introductions (\\i..)"
msgstr "Toktok long ol buk (i..)"

#: temp.glade:20820
msgid "Print the Book Introductions which\n"
"appear at the beginning of each book.\n"
"Includes markers like: \\is \\ip \\im \\ili etc."
msgstr "Prentim ol tok bilong kirap long buk, na putim ol maker olsem: \\is \\ip \\im \\ili etc."

#: temp.glade:20836
msgid "Introductory Outlines"
msgstr "Ol Tok Bilong Kirap"

#: temp.glade:20837
msgid "Enable introductory outlines"
msgstr "Toktok long ol samting yu laik mekim"

#: temp.glade:20841
msgid "Print the Introductory Outlines which\n"
"appear at the beginning of each book.\n"
"Includes markers: \\io1 ... \\io4 \\ior \\iot"
msgstr "Prentim ol stori bilong kirap bilong buk."

#: temp.glade:20857
msgid "Right-align \\ior With Tabbed Leaders"
msgstr "Toktok wantaim ol man i gat nem"

#: temp.glade:20858
msgid "Enable Right-aligned outlines with leaders"
msgstr "Mekim ol samting i stret wantaim tingting bilong ol lida"

#: temp.glade:20862
msgid "This will right-align and add leader tabs (. . . .) before the \\ior numbers for a pretty Intro Outline Table."
msgstr "Dispela bai mekim na ol i putim ol liklik liklik tab (. . . .) paslain long ol namba bilong ol dispela namba bilong kamapim wanpela naispela Intro Outline Table."

#: temp.glade:20874
msgid "Filter Glossary to Only Include Entries Used in the Text"
msgstr "Filtim ol tok bilong ol tok i stap long ol tok bilong en"

#: temp.glade:20875
msgid "Filter glossary"
msgstr "Ol tok bilong ol piksa"

#: temp.glade:20879
msgid "This option is only available if the GLO book\n"
"is also selected.\n"
"If you have large glossary with many entries \n"
"but are only printing a small selection of books, \n"
"you may benefit from this option which will \n"
"strip out any entries from the Glossary which\n"
"are not marked-up in the text of the selected \n"
"book(s) or chapter(s).\n"
"i.e. only the \\w marked-up\\w* entries in the \n"
"selected books/chapters will show in the glossary."
msgstr "Sapos yu gat bikpela buk GLO na planti tok i stap long en, tasol yu prinim liklik buk tasol, yu ken yusim dispela opsen na rausim ol tok i stap long buk GLO na i no stap long ol tok bilong buk o sapta yu makim."

#: temp.glade:20900
msgid "Start All Other Chapters on a New Page"
msgstr "Statim Ol Narapela Sapta Long Nupela Pes"

#: temp.glade:20901
msgid "Start every chapter on a new page"
msgstr "Kirapim olgeta sapta long nupela pes"

#: temp.glade:20905
msgid "Use this option to force a page break before\n"
"every chapter. This is most commonly used\n"
"for testing materials when each chapter needs\n"
"to be printed and given to a different person."
msgstr "Yu ken yusim dispela opsen long mekim wanpela pes i bruk paslain long olgeta sapta."

#: temp.glade:20920
msgid "Start 1st Chapter on a New Page"
msgstr "Kirapim Namba 1 Sapta Long Nupela Pes"

#: temp.glade:20921
msgid "Start new page after introduction"
msgstr "Statim nupela pes bihain long yu bin putim"

#: temp.glade:20925
msgid "Use this option to automatically make a page \n"
"break after a book's introduction section. \n"
"The break will come right before the \\c 1 marker."
msgstr "Yu ken yusim dispela opsen bilong mekim wanpela pes i bruk bihain long hap bilong stori long buk."

#: temp.glade:20946
msgid "Beginning and Ending Material"
msgstr "Ol Tok Bilong Statim na Tok Bilong Pinis"

#: temp.glade:20984
msgid "Hide First Verse Number"
msgstr "Haitim Namba Bilong Namba Wan Ves"

#: temp.glade:20985
msgid "Hide first verse number"
msgstr "Haitim namba bilong namba wan ves"

#: temp.glade:20989
msgid "It is quite common to hide the first verse\n"
"number - especially when following a\n"
"drop-cap chapter number. By default this\n"
"option is on. If you prefer to see verse\n"
"number 1, then uncheck this option."
msgstr "Sapos yu laik lukim namba 1 lain, orait yu no ken makim dispela lain."

#: temp.glade:21006
msgid "Keep Repeated Words Together"
msgstr "Tingim Ol Tok i Stap Long Tok Pisin"

#: temp.glade:21007
msgid "Keep repeated words together"
msgstr "Mekim wankain tok"

#: temp.glade:21011
msgid "This option encourages re-duplicated\n"
"words (i.e. those which are intentionally\n"
"repeated) to come together on the same line\n"
"by inserting a NoBreakSpace between them.\n"
"For example, \"gama gama\", or \"kala kala\" \n"
"need to be stuck together (with a NBSP)\n"
"in order to be read meaningfully.\n"
"However, if there are many of these in the\n"
"language, then it may create other unwanted\n"
"typesetting issues. Use with care!"
msgstr "Dispela opsen i kirapim ol tok i kamap planti (ol tok i gat planti hap tok) long kam wantaim long wankain lain long rot bilong putim wanpela NoBreakSpace namel long ol. Olsem, \"gama gama\", o \"kala kala\" i mas pas wantaim (wanpela NBSP) bilong ritim gut. Tasol sapos planti bilong ol dispela tok i stap long tokples, dispela inap kamapim ol narapela hevi long pasin bilong raitim ol tok."

#: temp.glade:21032
msgid "Indent First Paragraph"
msgstr "Namba wan hap bilong dispela hap"

#: temp.glade:21033
msgid "Indent first paragraph after section heading"
msgstr "Namba wan hap bilong dispela hap i kamap bihain long het bilong seksen"

#: temp.glade:21037
msgid "If this option is unchecked, it will make the 1st\n"
"\\p(aragraph) after a Section Heading appear as\n"
"a \\m(argin) paragraph with no indentation."
msgstr "Sapos yu no makim dispela opesen, dispela bai mekim namba wan hap bilong paragraf bihain long Het bilong Seksen i kamap olsem hap bilong paragraf i no gat ol hap i stap insait long en."

#: temp.glade:21052
msgid "Hanging Poetry Verse Numbers"
msgstr "Ol Namba Bilong Ol Tok Bilong Buk"

#: temp.glade:21053
msgid "Use hanging verse number for poetry"
msgstr "Yusim namba bilong ves bilong raitim ol tok bilong buk"

#: temp.glade:21057
msgid "Verse numbers for Poetry elements all\n"
"line up vertically on the margin, and\n"
"Verse Bridges (3-4) also stack vertically."
msgstr "Ol namba bilong ol ves bilong ol tok bilong Poetry i stap long sait bilong en, na ol lain bilong Verse Bridges (3-4) tu i stap long sait bilong en."

#: temp.glade:21072
msgid "Prevent Verse Widow Words "
msgstr "Lukautim Tok Bilong Wido"

#: temp.glade:21073
msgid "Prevent verse widow words"
msgstr "No ken mekim tok long ol meri i dai pinis"

#: temp.glade:21077
msgid "This option prevents short words (of\n"
"3 characters or less) from occurring\n"
"AFTER a verse begins near the end of \n"
"a line."
msgstr "Dispela rot i save pasim ol liklik tok (ol i no winim 3-pela mak) long kamap bihain long wanpela ves i kirap klostu long pinis bilong wanpela lain."

#: temp.glade:21092
msgid "Prevent Orphan Words"
msgstr "No Ken Tok Long Ol Tok i No Gutpela"

#: temp.glade:21093
msgid "Prevent orphan words at end of paragraph or start of line."
msgstr "No ken putim ol tok i no gat nem long pinis bilong paragraf o kirap bilong lain."

#: temp.glade:21097
msgid "This option limits short words\n"
"at the ends of paragraphs from \n"
"occuring on a line on their own.\n"
"It also prevents short words at \n"
"the end of sentences from starting \n"
"on a new line."
msgstr "Dispela pasin i save pasim ol liklik tok i stap long pinis bilong paragraf long kamap long wanpela lain stret. Na tu, em i save pasim ol liklik tok i stap long pinis bilong tok long kirap long nupela lain."

#: temp.glade:21114
msgid "Justify Paragraphs"
msgstr "Stori Long As Bilong Ol Paragraf"

#: temp.glade:21115
msgid "Justify paragraphs"
msgstr "Stori long as bilong ol paragraf"

#: temp.glade:21119
msgid "By default the text will be fully justified.\n"
"If you prefer a ragged edge, then uncheck\n"
"this option.\n\n"
"Note that a justification setting of \"Justify\"\n"
"in a style is subject to this setting."
msgstr "Sapos yu laik bai ol tok i stap long pes i stret olgeta, orait yu mas rausim dispela mak."

#: temp.glade:21142 temp.glade:31469
msgid "Section Headings"
msgstr "Ol Het Tok Bilong Ol Seksen"

#: temp.glade:21143
msgid "Enable section headings"
msgstr "Opim ol het tok bilong seksen"

#: temp.glade:21147
msgid "Uncheck this option if you don't want\n"
"to print any Section Headings.\n"
"Unchecking this option will ALSO \n"
"uncheck the Parallel Passage Refs."
msgstr "No ken makim dispela hap sapos yu no laik prinim ol Het bilong Seksen."

#: temp.glade:21170 temp.glade:21222 temp.glade:21477 temp.glade:21529
#: temp.glade:21910 temp.glade:26670
msgid "Click to edit the marker's properties on the Styles tab."
msgstr "Klik long Edit ol property bilong maker long Stiles tab."

#: temp.glade:21195
msgid "Parallel Passage Refs "
msgstr "Ol Tok i Stap Long Ol Hap i Gat Stretpela Stret"

#: temp.glade:21196
msgid "Enable parallel passage references"
msgstr "Toktok long ol hap i stap wankain"

#: temp.glade:21200
msgid "Uncheck this option to hide all the\n"
"Parallel Pasage References which\n"
"occur below Section Headings."
msgstr "No ken makim dispela rot bilong haitim olgeta Parallel Passage References i stap aninit long ol Het Tok bilong Seksen."

#: temp.glade:21246
msgid "Hide Empty Verses"
msgstr "Haitim Ol Ves i No Gat Tok"

#: temp.glade:21247
msgid "Show or hide empty verses"
msgstr "Makim o haitim ol hap bilong buk"

#: temp.glade:21251
msgid "Do not print any empty chapters or verses.\n"
"Useful for when only part of the text has been\n"
"drafted but you still need a printout of whatever\n"
"has been translated so far."
msgstr "Yu no ken prinim ol hap na ves i stap nating, na dispela inap helpim yu taim yu raitim pinis sampela hap bilong Baibel, tasol yu mas prinim yet ol tok yu bin tanim."

#: temp.glade:21268
msgid "Show '...'"
msgstr "Kamapim..."

#: temp.glade:21269
msgid "Show elipsis in place of missing verses"
msgstr "Lukim ol hap i no stap long ol ves"

#: temp.glade:21273
msgid "Indicate using ellipsis that verses and/or \n"
"entire chapters are missing by placing '...'\n"
"in the text to alert the reader that some\n"
"parts of the text have been skipped."
msgstr "Tok olsem ol ves na/o olgeta sapta i lus, na putim \"\"... long rait bilong kirapim man long ritim ol tok i lus."

#: temp.glade:21300
msgid "Marginal Verses:"
msgstr "Ol Ves Bilong Makim Tok:"

#: temp.glade:21301
msgid "Show verse numbers in the margin"
msgstr "Makim namba bilong ol ves long sait"

#: temp.glade:21305
msgid "Some language communities prefer the\n"
"verse numbers to be displayed in a\n"
"vertical stack NEXT to the text (rather\n"
"than within the text itself). If that is\n"
"what is required, check this option\n"
"and also adjust the width of that\n"
"column to fit the verse numbers."
msgstr "Sampela lain i save laikim ol namba bilong ol ves long stap long wanpela hap i stap klostu long ol ves (no insait long ol ves yet)."

#: temp.glade:21327 temp.glade:21347
msgid "Marginal verses are usually placed\n"
"on the left of the text, but can be\n"
"positioned elsewhere if needed."
msgstr "Ol i save putim ol ves i stap long sait han kais bilong tok, tasol sapos i gat wok, ol inap putim ol long narapela hap."

#: temp.glade:21332
msgid "Position on Page: "
msgstr "Ples long pes: "

#: temp.glade:21342
msgid "Horizontal position of marginal verses"
msgstr "Ples bilong ol hap bilong ol ves"

#: temp.glade:21376 temp.glade:21394
msgid "This is the amount of space to the left\n"
"of the column of text to accommodate \n"
"marginal verse numbers. (pts)"
msgstr "Dispela em hap hap i stap long han kais bilong kolon bilong rait bilong putim namba bilong ol ves i stap long sait bilong rait. (pts)"

#: temp.glade:21381
msgid "Col Width (pts):"
msgstr "Long Col Width (pts):"

#: temp.glade:21391
msgid "Column width for marginal verses"
msgstr "Brait bilong kolumn bilong ol hap bilong ol ves"

#: temp.glade:21447
msgid "Chapter numbers"
msgstr "Namba bilong ol sapta"

#: temp.glade:21448
msgid "Show chapter numbers"
msgstr "Makim namba bilong sapta"

#: temp.glade:21452
msgid "Uncheck this option to hide all chapter \n"
"numbers - making the publication read\n"
"more like an ordinary book.\n\n"
"Note that there is another option lower down\n"
"in the next section which will only \"Hide Chapter\n"
"Number in Single Chapter Books\"."
msgstr "Lukim olsem i gat narapela opsen long hap daunbilo long narapela seksen we i tok \"Hide Chapter Number in Single Chapter Books\"."

#: temp.glade:21502
msgid "Verse Numbers"
msgstr "Namba bilong Ol Ves"

#: temp.glade:21503
msgid "Show verse numbers"
msgstr "Makim namba bilong ol ves"

#: temp.glade:21507
msgid "Uncheck this option to hide all verse \n"
"numbers - making the publication read\n"
"more like an ordinary book."
msgstr "No ken makim dispela hap bilong pasim namba bilong ol ves - ⁠olsem bai buk i luk olsem wanpela buk nating."

#: temp.glade:21554
msgid "Include Scripture Text"
msgstr "Kamapim Ol Ves"

#: temp.glade:21555
msgid "Show or hide scripture text"
msgstr "Makim o haitim ol skripsa"

#: temp.glade:21559
msgid "Normally you should leave this checked.\n\n"
"BUT... if you require a printout of just the\n"
"book introductions (usually for the\n"
"purpose of final checking, or looking\n"
"for consistency) then this option can\n"
"be unchecked (to omit the verse text\n"
"and everything else in the main body)."
msgstr "Sapos yu laik printim ol tok bilong kirap long buk (olsem bilong skelim gut ol tok bilong buk o bilong kamapim klia olsem tok i stret wantaim tok bilong buk) orait yu no ken makim dispela tok (long rausim ol ves na olgeta narapela tok i stap long buk)."

#: temp.glade:21608
msgid "Use Special Features\n"
"for These Books:"
msgstr "Yusim Ol Narapela Tok Bilong Ol Dispela Buk:"

#: temp.glade:21610
msgid "Enable special features for some books"
msgstr "Opim ol narapela buk"

#: temp.glade:21614
msgid "Some Poetical books like the Psalms, and maybe even\n"
"Proverbs look better without drop-cap chapter numbers.\n"
"Instead, they can use a prefix like \"Chapter\" or \"Psalm\"\n"
"at the start of the chapter.\n"
"Note: If the text already has one or more \\cl markers, then\n"
"these settings will overrirde what has been set in the text."
msgstr "Sampela buk bilong ol Singsing, na sampela buk bilong Sindaun, i luk gutpela moa sapos ol i no putim namba bilong sapta long hap tok. Ol i ken putim namba olsem \"Kapta\" o \"Sapela\" long kirap bilong sapta."

#: temp.glade:21632
msgid "List of books with special features enabled"
msgstr "Ol buk i gat ol narapela narapela samting i stap"

#: temp.glade:21636
msgid "Add the 3-letter book codes for any books that\n"
"this \"Chapter Label\" setting should be applied to.\n\n"
"Note: If this list of books is left empty, then this\n"
"setting will be applied to ALL books"
msgstr "Toksave: Sapos dispela lista i no gat wanpela tok, dispela toksave bai kamap long olgeta buk"

#: temp.glade:21642
msgid "e.g. PSA PRO"
msgstr "P.S.A. PRO"

#: temp.glade:21652
msgid "Chapter label (for special feature books)"
msgstr "Ol buk i gat nem bilong ol (long ol buk bilong ol narapela buk)"

#: temp.glade:21656
msgid "The chapter “label” to be used when rendering\n"
"chapter divisions as headings (instead of drop-cap\n"
"numerals). For example, \"Chapter\" or \"Psalm\".\n\n"
"If you want the chapter number to appear centered\n"
"and above the Section Header WITHOUT any preceding\n"
"text, then just put the code \\\\ZWNBSP in here. This will\n"
"insert a Zero Width Non-Break Space."
msgstr "Sapos yu laik bai namba bilong sapta i stap namel na antap long het bilong sapta, na i no gat wanpela hap tok i stap paslain long en, orait putim kod \\\\ZWNBSP long hap hia. Dispela bai putim wanpela hap i no gat hap bilong brukim."

#: temp.glade:21676
msgid "The chapter “label” to be used when rendering\n"
"chapter divisions as headings (instead of drop-cap\n"
"numerals). For example, \"Chapter\" or \"Psalm\".\n\n"
"If you want the chapter number to appear centered\n"
"and above the Section Header WITHOUT any preceding\n"
"text, then just put the code \\ZWNBSP in here. This will\n"
"insert a Zero Width Non Break Space."
msgstr "Sapos yu laik bai namba bilong sapta i stap namel na antap long het bilong sapta, orait putim kod \\ZWNBSP long hap hia. Dispela bai putim wanpela namba i no gat hap bilong brukim."

#: temp.glade:21685
msgid "Chapter\n"
"Label:"
msgstr "Nem bilong hap:"

#: temp.glade:21696
msgid "Use One/Two Column\n"
"Layout for These Books:"
msgstr "Yusim wanpela o tupela kolum long ol dispela buk:"

#: temp.glade:21698
msgid "Enable 1 or 2 column layout for certain books"
msgstr "Toksave long ol hap bilong buk yu laik putim long wanpela o tupela kolom"

#: temp.glade:21702 temp.glade:21756
msgid "Some books (e.g. Introduction, Glossary, Psalms, and \n"
"maybe even Proverbs) look better formatted as single\n"
"column, even though most of the books are typeset\n"
"in two column layout. This allows the same publication\n"
"to have both single and double column layouts.\n\n"
"Add the 3-letter book codes for any books that should \n"
"be typeset using a different column layout. \n\n"
"Note that if the layout for the entire publication\n"
"is set to single column, then the books listed here\n"
"would use double-column layout. Conversely, if \n"
"the publication is set as double-column (on the \n"
"layout page) then any books listed here would\n"
"be set in single-column layout."
msgstr "Sampela buk (olsem Introduction, Glossary, Psalms, na ating ol Sindaun) i luk gutpela moa sapos ol i putim ol tok long wanpela kolom tasol, maski planti buk i gat tupela kolom tasol. Dispela i mekim na wanpela buk inap gat tupela kolom tasol. Tasol sapos ol buk i gat tupela kolon (long pes bilong ol buk i stap long pes) orait ol buk i stap long dispela pes i gat wanpela kolon tasol."

#: temp.glade:21729 temp.glade:21730
msgid "Optimize Layout for Poetry Books"
msgstr "Stretim Gut Ol Tok Bilong Buk Bilong Poem"

#: temp.glade:21734
msgid "Trying to get  columns of poetry to balance often\n"
"creates all sorts of unforeseen issues and unwanted\n"
"whitespace. This option allows columns to be \n"
"unbalanced, which might improve the overall look.\n"
"But note that it also allows Widow and Orphan \n"
"lines to occur, which is a negative side-effect."
msgstr "Taim ol i traim long stretim ol pos i stap long pes, dispela i save kamapim ol hevi na ol hap hap i no stret. Dispela pasin i save mekim na ol pos i no stap stret, na dispela inap helpim ol long luk gut moa."

#: temp.glade:21753
msgid "List of books with different column settings"
msgstr "Ol buk i gat narapela narapela kolumn"

#: temp.glade:21772
msgid "e.g. FRT INT PSA PRO BAK GLO"
msgstr "FRT INT PSA PRO BAK GLO"

#: temp.glade:21786
msgid "Show Chapter\n"
"Numbers in:"
msgstr "Lukim Namba Bilong Kapitol long:"

#: temp.glade:21797
msgid "Define how glossary words should appear in the text"
msgstr "Tokim ol man long ol tok ol i mas yusim long ol tok bilong buk"

#: temp.glade:21800
msgid "Glossary words may be marked up \n"
"with \\w glossary\\w* tags. Specify\n"
"how these words should appear\n"
"in the printed output.\n\n"
"If you wish to apply your own custom\n"
"styling to \\w then select the \\w ...\\w*\n"
"character style option."
msgstr "Sapos yu laik putim ol tok bilong yu yet long ol tok bilong ol tokples, orait makim dispela opsen bilong pasin bilong ol tokples."

#: temp.glade:21810
msgid "Glossary Word Appearance:"
msgstr "Toktok bilong Baibel:"

#: temp.glade:21820
msgid "Markup for glossary words in text"
msgstr "Makim ol tok bilong ol tok i stap long ol buk"

#: temp.glade:21824
msgid "Glossary words are marked up with\n"
"special \\w glossary\\w* tags. Specify\n"
"how these words should be highlighted\n"
"in the printed output.\n\n"
"The final option \\w keeps|markup\\w* as\n"
"it is without removing any parameters\n"
"such as Strong's numbers."
msgstr "Ol i save putim ol mak long ol tok ol i kolim long ol buk bilong ol. Ol i save putim ol mak long ol tok ol i kolim long buk ol i raitim long en."

#: temp.glade:21851
msgid "Single Chapter Books"
msgstr "Ol Buk i Gat Wanpela Sapta"

#: temp.glade:21852
msgid "Show chapters in single chapter books"
msgstr "Lukim ol sapta long ol buk i gat wanpela sapta tasol"

#: temp.glade:21856
msgid "Select this option to show the 1 at the beginning\n"
"of books that only have a single chapter (OBA, PHM,\n"
"2JN, 3JN, JUD, etc.)"
msgstr "Makim dispela opsen bilong soim namba 1 long kirap bilong ol buk i gat wanpela sapta tasol (OBA, PHM, 2JN, 3JN, JUD, na ol narapela)"

#: temp.glade:21872
msgid "Non-Scripture Books"
msgstr "Ol Buk i No Kam Long Baibel"

#: temp.glade:21873
msgid "Show chapters in non-scripture books"
msgstr "Makim ol sapta long ol buk i no gat Baibel long en"

#: temp.glade:21877
msgid "Peripheral books often have more than one\n"
"\"chapter\" but do not need the chapter number\n"
"to be printed. By default, PTXprint removes\n"
"the chapter numbers from non-scripture books.\n"
"If you need it to retain (and show) those chapter\n"
"numbers then check this option."
msgstr "Ol buk bilong ol narapela hap i gat planti \"kap\" tasol ol i no gat wok long prinim namba bilong sapta. Sapos yu laik kisim ol dispela namba bilong sapta, orait sekim dispela opsen."

#: temp.glade:21930
msgid "The \\zglm style is used to format the\n"
"floor brackets used in glossary markup.\n\n"
"Click to edit the marker's properties on the Styles tab."
msgstr "Ol i save yusim pasin \\zglm long putim ol hap hap bilong ol hap i stap namel long ol hap bilong ol hap ol i kolim ol tok ples."

#: temp.glade:21972
msgid "Other Features"
msgstr "Ol Narapela Samting"

#: temp.glade:21991
msgid "Main settings to control the \n"
"beginning and ending of books,\n"
"and options for what should be\n"
"included in the Main Body of text.\n"
"Also settings for special books."
msgstr "Ol bikpela sait bilong bosim kirap na pinis bilong ol buk, na ol samting yu laik putim insait long Main Body of text."

#: temp.glade:21997
msgid "Body"
msgstr "Bodi bilong en"

#: temp.glade:22051 temp.glade:23388
msgid "Show Callers in Notes Area"
msgstr "Lukim Ol Kalia Long Notes"

#: temp.glade:22052
msgid "Show footnote callers in notes area"
msgstr "Lukim ol man i kolim ol tok daunbilo long hap bilong ol tok daunbilo"

#: temp.glade:22057
msgid "Usually the \"Caller\" symbol is also shown\n"
"in the notes area which helps the reader \n"
"quickly find the footnote from the text."
msgstr "Planti taim ol i save putim piksa \"Caller\" long hap bilong ol not na dispela i helpim man i ritim long painim kwik not long ol tok."

#: temp.glade:22073 temp.glade:23410
msgid "Reset Callers on Page"
msgstr "Reset Ol Caller Long Pes"

#: temp.glade:22074
msgid "Reset footnote callers on each page"
msgstr "Resietim ol lain i kolim ol tok daunbilo long olgeta pes"

#: temp.glade:22078 temp.glade:23415
msgid "If this is checked, then the sequence of \n"
"callers starts again from the 1st item in\n"
"the list of callers specified.\n\n"
"Note that this feature doesn't always take\n"
"effect straight away. You may need to hit\n"
"Print a second time before it applies."
msgstr "Sapos yu makim dispela, orait ol man i ring i kirap gen long namba wan hap long lista bilong ol man i ring. Tingim olsem dispela pasin i no save kamap kwiktaim. Ating yu mas print gen paslain long yu mekim dispela wok."

#: temp.glade:22104 temp.glade:23292
msgid "Show Callers\n"
"in the Text:"
msgstr ""

#: temp.glade:22106
msgid "Show Footnote Callers in the Text"
msgstr "Makim Ol Tok Bilong Makim Ol Tok"

#: temp.glade:22110
msgid "A \"Caller\" is a symbol (in the text) which\n"
"alerts the reader that there is further\n"
"information (in this case a footnote\n"
"at the bottom of the page). Ideally, \n"
"the caller should be distinct from the\n"
"rest of the text, so a symbol works\n"
"well if supported by the font. Otherwise\n"
"the letters of the alphabet can be used.\n\n"
"Separate callers with a comma (no spaces).\n"
"For example: a,b,c,d,e,f,g,h, etc.\n"
"or:  †,‡,§,∥,#    or: ✶,☆,✦,✪\n\n"
"If you do not see the callers you are \n"
"expecting in the PDF, then try using \n"
"the \"Override...\" setting above.\n"
msgstr ""

#: temp.glade:22141
msgid "Footnote Caller Sequence Entry"
msgstr "Toktok long pes bilong pes"

#: temp.glade:22145 temp.glade:23332
msgid "These callers should automatically be loaded from\n"
"the settings in the Paratext project, but can be\n"
"modified here if needed.\n"
"(Use to button on the right to Reload if needed.)\n\n"
"Separate callers with a comma (no spaces).\n"
"For example: a,b,c,d,e,f,g,h, etc.\n"
"or:  †,‡,§,∥,#    or: ✶,☆,✦,✪"
msgstr "Ol dispela man i save ring i mas kisim ol dispela namba long ol sait bilong Paratext, tasol sapos yu nidim yu ken senisim ol dispela namba long hia. (Yu ken yusim boten long han sut bilong Reload sapos yu nidim.) Ol narapela man i save ring i mas putim kom (no gat hap hap). Olsem: a,b,c,d,e,f,g,h, etc. o: †,‡,§,,# o: ,☆,,"

#: temp.glade:22165
msgid "Reload footnote callers from Paratext"
msgstr "Reload ol fòtnot sumatin long Paratext"

#: temp.glade:22169
msgid "Clicking this button will reload\n"
"the footnote callers from the\n"
"Paratext project settings.\n\n"
"If the callers have not been defined \n"
"in the Paratext project, or are already\n"
"showing, then a default set will appear."
msgstr "Sapos yu klik long dispela boton, dispela bai kirapim bek ol man i save ringim ol tok daunbilo long ol sait bilong Paratext projek. Sapos ol i no bin makim ol dispela man long Paratext projek, o ol i stap pinis, orait wanpela default set bai kamap."

#: temp.glade:22201
msgid "Override hidden/automatic Footnote caller settings"
msgstr "Ritim ol sait bilong ol man i kolim ol tok i stap hait/automatik"

#: temp.glade:22202
msgid "Override Footnote Settings in Text"
msgstr "Rausim Ol Futnot Insait Long Ol Tok"

#: temp.glade:22206
msgid "The Footnotes specified in Paratext use\n"
"\\x +(plus) to cycle through the callers,\n"
"or \\x - (minus) to omit the caller.\n\n"
"If this option is enabled, the Show Callers\n"
"settings below will override whatever\n"
"has been specified within the text itself."
msgstr "Ol Footnotes i stap long Paratext i save yusim \\x +(plus) long tanim ol man i singaut, o \\x - (minus) long rausim man i singaut. Sapos dispela opsen i stap, ol senis long Show Callers bai senisim ol samting ol i bin makim insait long teks yet."

#: temp.glade:22225 temp.glade:22226
msgid "Start Each Footnote on a New Line"
msgstr "Kirapim nupela lain long ol tok i stap daunbilo"

#: temp.glade:22230
msgid "Normally footnotes are arranged one after\n"
"the other to form a block of text. But if you \n"
"require each footnote to start on its own new\n"
"line then set this option."
msgstr "Ol i save putim ol tok daunbilo i go i kam bilong kamapim wanpela hap tok. Tasol sapos yu laik bai olgeta tok daunbilo i mas stat long nupela lain bilong en, orait putim dispela opsen."

#: temp.glade:22253
msgid "Click to edit the Footnote properties on the Styles tab."
msgstr "Klik long Edit Footnote property long Styles tab."

#: temp.glade:22267 temp.glade:23154
msgid "End Notes"
msgstr "Ol Tok Bilong Pinis"

#: temp.glade:22268
msgid "Placement of footnotes: End notes"
msgstr "Ples bilong putim ol tok daunbilo: Ol tok daunbilo bilong pinisim tok"

#: temp.glade:22272
msgid "This option will prevent footnotes showing\n"
"on each page, but will gather them together\n"
"and place them all at the end of the book."
msgstr "Dispela rot bai pasim rot long ol tok i stap daunbilo long ol pes, na bai ol i stap wantaim na putim olgeta long pinis bilong buk."

#: temp.glade:22290 temp.glade:23177
msgid "End of Column"
msgstr "Pinis Bilong Kolom"

#: temp.glade:22291
msgid "Placement of footnotes: End of column"
msgstr "Ples bilong ol tok daunbilo: Ples bilong pinis bilong kolom"

#: temp.glade:22295
msgid "Use this option (only available in 2-column\n"
"layout) to show the footnotes at the end\n"
"of the 2nd column of text."
msgstr "Yu ken yusim dispela opesen (ol i wokim long 2-pela kolon tasol) bilong soim ol tok daunbilo long pinis bilong namba 2 kolon bilong teks."

#: temp.glade:22315 temp.glade:23202
msgid "End of Page"
msgstr "Pinis Bilong Pes"

#: temp.glade:22316
msgid "Placement of footnotes: End of page"
msgstr "Ples bilong ol tok daunbilo: Ples daunbilo"

#: temp.glade:22320
msgid "Footnotes (and cross-references) are\n"
"usually placed at the end of each page.\n"
msgstr ""

#: temp.glade:22339
msgid "Footnote placement: End of page"
msgstr "Ples bilong ol tok daunbilo: Ples daunbilo bilong pes"

#: temp.glade:22344
msgid "Placement of Footnotes:"
msgstr "Ples bilong putim ol tok daunbilo:"

#: temp.glade:22379 temp.glade:24461 temp.glade:25360
msgid "Space Below Rule (pt)"
msgstr "Hap Raun i Stap aninit long Lo (pt)"

#: temp.glade:22396 temp.glade:24478 temp.glade:25377
msgid "Space Above Rule (pt)"
msgstr "Ol samting i stap antap long ol lo (pt)"

#: temp.glade:22411 temp.glade:22680 temp.glade:24514 temp.glade:24755
#: temp.glade:25302 temp.glade:25392
msgid "The vertical space between the body text and the\n"
"area containing footnotes and cross-references.\n\n"
"If the Footnote Rule is not shown, the vertical\n"
"space will still be calculated as the Space Above\n"
"plus the Space Below (the imaginary) Rule."
msgstr "Dispela mak i makim hap namel long bodi bilong tok na hap i gat ol tok daunbilo na ol tok i stap long en. Sapos yu no lukim dispela lo, dispela mak bai stap yet olsem hap antap na hap daunbilo (dispela lo i no tru)."

#: temp.glade:22418 temp.glade:25399
msgid "Space Separating\n"
"Text From Notes:"
msgstr "Ol hap hap bilong rait i stap namel long ol tok:"

#: temp.glade:22428
msgid "Space above footnote rule"
msgstr "Hap antap long lo bilong footnot"

#: temp.glade:22431 temp.glade:25412
msgid "The vertical space between the main\n"
"text body and the footnote rule.\n\n"
"Note: if you make this value less than the descenders\n"
"of the last lines of text, then the footnotes will push\n"
"down into the footer area. If you see this happening,\n"
"increase this value to trigger an earlier page break to\n"
"solve the problem."
msgstr "Dispela mak i stap namel long hap bilong bikpela rait na lo bilong ol tok daunbilo. Tingim: sapos yu mekim dispela namba i liklik moa long namba bilong ol lain i stap daunbilo long laspela lain bilong rait, orait ol tok daunbilo bai go daun long hap bilong ol tok daunbilo. Sapos yu lukim dispela samting i kamap, skruim dispela namba i go antap na bai yu opim pes pastaim bilong stretim dispela hevi."

#: temp.glade:22456
msgid "Space below footnote rule"
msgstr "Hap i stap aninit long lo bilong not"

#: temp.glade:22459 temp.glade:25440
msgid "This is the vertical space/gap (pts) between\n"
"the rule and the footnotes."
msgstr "Dispela em ples namel long lo na ol tok daunbilo."

#: temp.glade:22494 temp.glade:22495
msgid "Show Footnote Rule"
msgstr "Makim Tok i stap daunbilo"

#: temp.glade:22499 temp.glade:25341
msgid "This is the horizontal rule separating\n"
"the body text from the footnote area."
msgstr "Dispela lo i save katim hap bilong ol tok i stap long pes na hap bilong ol tok i stap daunbilo."

#: temp.glade:22528
msgid "Footnote rule: Indent"
msgstr "Lo bilong not: Ineks"

#: temp.glade:22531 temp.glade:24606 temp.glade:25153
msgid "This is the amount to indent the rule."
msgstr "Dispela em namba bilong mak bilong dispela mak."

#: temp.glade:22548
msgid "Footnote rule: Length"
msgstr "Lo bilong tok daunbilo: Longpela"

#: temp.glade:22551 temp.glade:24626 temp.glade:25173
msgid "The length of the rule as a percentage\n"
"of the column/page width."
msgstr "Longpela bilong dispela lo olsem hap bilong mak bilong longpela bilong kolom/i go long pes."

#: temp.glade:22570
msgid "Footnote rule: Line Thickness"
msgstr "Lo bilong ol tok daunbilo: Stretpela mak"

#: temp.glade:22573 temp.glade:24648 temp.glade:25195
msgid "The thickness of the rule."
msgstr "Dispela lo i stret."

#: temp.glade:22592
msgid "Footnote rule: Horizontal position"
msgstr "Lo bilong ol tok daunbilo: Ples bilong wokabaut"

#: temp.glade:22617 temp.glade:24692 temp.glade:25239
msgid "Indent (mm)"
msgstr "Ol i mas kisim ol liklik hap bilong ol samting"

#: temp.glade:22634 temp.glade:24709 temp.glade:25256
msgid "Length (% of col)"
msgstr "Long (% of col)"

#: temp.glade:22650 temp.glade:24725 temp.glade:25272
msgid "Thickness (pt)"
msgstr "Mak bilong ol samting"

#: temp.glade:22687 temp.glade:24762 temp.glade:25309
msgid "Rule Positioning\n"
"and Parameters:"
msgstr "Tok bilong ol lain i bosim ol samting:"

#: temp.glade:22718 temp.glade:24793 temp.glade:25463
msgid "Rule and Space Settings"
msgstr "Ol Raun na Hap Hap"

#: temp.glade:22734 temp.glade:22735
msgid "Include Footnotes"
msgstr "Tokim Ol Man Long Ol Futnot"

#: temp.glade:22740
msgid "Select whether footnotes should \n"
"be included.\n\n"
"The specific settings for these are\n"
"located on the Footnotes tab."
msgstr "Makim sapos yu laik putim ol tok daunbilo o nogat. Ol senis bilong ol dispela tok daunbilo i stap long tab Tok daunbilo."

#: temp.glade:22772
msgid "Only show verse numbers from \\fr"
msgstr "Lukim ol namba bilong ol ves long \\fr tasol"

#: temp.glade:22776
msgid "The footnote reference \\fr usually\n"
"includes the chapter & verse number\n"
"like this 3:16. If you prefer to hide the\n"
"chapter, so that only 16 is shown, then\n"
"enable this option."
msgstr "Long ol tok i stap daunbilo long pes, ol i save putim namba bilong sapta na ves olsem 3:16 long pes."

#: temp.glade:22828
msgid "Add a Colon ':' After \\fq and \\xq"
msgstr "Tokim long ':' bihain long \\fq na \\xq"

#: temp.glade:22829
msgid "Add colon after quoted text in notes"
msgstr "Toktok i gat tok i stap long en"

#: temp.glade:22833
msgid "Some projects prefer to separate the\n"
"Quoted text from the footnote text\n"
"with a colon ':' which helps keep the\n"
"elements visually distinct."
msgstr "Sampela projek i save yusim tupela sentens long katim ol tok i stap long ol tok i stap daunbilo long ol tok bilong Baibel, na dispela i helpim ol tok i stap daunbilo long ol tok."

#: temp.glade:22850 temp.glade:22851
msgid "Keep Book Names and Refs Together"
msgstr "Stap wantaim nem bilong buk na ol man i skelim buk"

#: temp.glade:22855
msgid "This option inserts a No-Break Space (\\u00A0)\n"
"between the book name and the Ch:Vs refs\n"
"so that they don't get split across lines.\n\n"
"Note:  This setting currently has no effect on\n"
"cross-references imported from external lists."
msgstr "Dispela opsen i putim wanpela No-Break Space (\\u00A0) namel long nem bilong buk na ol Ch:Vs ref olsem ol i no bruk long ol lain."

#: temp.glade:22875 temp.glade:22876
msgid "Show All Glossary Entries as Footnotes"
msgstr "Lukim Olgeta Tok Bilong Buk Baibel Long Ol Futnot"

#: temp.glade:22880
msgid "Glossary entries for ALL marked-up\n"
"Biblical Terms on each page can be\n"
"made to appear as footnotes.\n\n"
"Glossary \\w markup|mark\\w* looks like\n"
"this in the USFM text file.\n\n"
"This feature is extremely useful when\n"
"producing printouts for comprehension\n"
"testing (where  Key Biblical Terms in the\n"
"passage which have Glossary Entries also\n"
"need to be checked for understanding)."
msgstr "Long ol pes i gat ol tok bilong Baibel, yu ken putim ol tok i stap long ol tok i stap daunbilo bilong pes. Dispela tok i stap long ol pes i stap daunbilo bilong pes."

#: temp.glade:22905
msgid "The horizontal space between notes that are being\n"
"run together as a single paragraph can be set here. \n"
"The default space is calculated as 33% between \n"
"min & max values.\n\n"
"For example if min=6pt and max=15pt then the \n"
"default horizontal space between notes would be 9pt.\n\n"
"If this control is disabled, it is because both the\n"
"Footnotes and Cross-References have been set\n"
"to start on a new line. (see \\f and \\x settings above)."
msgstr "Dispela hap graun namel long ol not bilong ol i stap wantaim olsem wanpela paragraf inap kamap long dispela hap. Dispela hap graun i stap namel long min & max i olsem 33%. Sapos min=6pt na max=15pt, orait hap graun namel long ol not bai stap 9pt. Sapos dispela hap graun i no stap, dispela i kamap long wanem, ol Footnotes na Cross-References i stat long nupela lain. (lukim ol sait bilong \\f na \\x antap)."

#: temp.glade:22917
msgid "Horizontal Space\n"
"Separating Notes:"
msgstr "Ol toksave bilong ol hap i stap antap:"

#: temp.glade:22927
msgid "Minimum Horizontal Space Separating Notes"
msgstr "Ol liklik hap hap graun i stap namel long ol narapela hap"

#: temp.glade:22930
msgid "This spacing is set in points (pts). Changing this will \n"
"increase or decrease the MINIMUM horizontal space\n"
"between notes that have been run together."
msgstr "Dispela hap mak i stap long ol poin (pts). Sapos yu senisim dispela hap mak, dispela bai mekim olsem hap mak i stap namel long ol not i bin ran wantaim i go bikpela o liklik."

#: temp.glade:22955
msgid "Maximum Horizontal Space Separating Notes"
msgstr "Ol toksave bilong katim hap i stap antap long ples"

#: temp.glade:22958
msgid "This spacing is set in points (pts). Changing this will \n"
"increase or decrease the MAXIMUM horizontal space\n"
"between notes that have been run together."
msgstr "Dispela hap mak i stap namel long ol tok i stap long ol poin (pts). Sapos yu senisim dispela hap mak bai mekim hap mak i stap namel long ol tok i stap wantaim i go bikpela o i go liklik."

#: temp.glade:22988
msgid "Minimum Space (pt)"
msgstr "Minimim Space (pt)"

#: temp.glade:23005
msgid "Maximum Space (pt)"
msgstr "Ples i bikpela tru (pt)"

#: temp.glade:23017
msgid "Vertical Space Between Footnoes and xRefs"
msgstr "Vertical Space Between Footnoes and xRefs Ol lek bilong lek na ol lek bilong lek"

#: temp.glade:23020 temp.glade:23045
msgid "When Footnotes and Cross-references are not blended\n"
"together in the same block then the Footnotes appear\n"
"in one block and the Cross-references in another block \n"
"just below them. This setting (pts) lets you adjust the \n"
"vertical space between these two sections."
msgstr "Taim yu no bungim ol Futnot na ol Kruse Referens wantaim long wanpela blok, orait ol Futnot bai kamap long wanpela blok na ol Kruse Referens bai kamap long narapela blok aninit long ol."

#: temp.glade:23052
msgid "Vertical Space Between\n"
"Footnotes and xRefs (pt):"
msgstr "Vertical Space Between Footnotes and xRefs (pt): Ol rait i stap namel long ol lo i stap daunbilo bilong buk na ol tok i stap long ol tok i stap daunbilo bilong buk"

#: temp.glade:23104
msgid "Miscellaneous Footnote Settings"
msgstr "Sampela Rot Bilong Makim Ol Futnot"

#: temp.glade:23155
msgid "Placement of cross-references: As End Notes"
msgstr "Ol i mas putim ol tok i stap long rot bilong ol narapela tok:"

#: temp.glade:23159
msgid "This option will prevent cross-references showing\n"
"on each page, but will gather them together\n"
"and place them all at the end of the book."
msgstr "Dispela rot bai pasim rot bilong ol tok i stap long olgeta pes, na bai bungim ol tok i stap long pinis bilong buk."

#: temp.glade:23178
msgid "Placement of cross-references: End of column"
msgstr "Ples bilong ol kru: Ples bilong kol"

#: temp.glade:23182
msgid "Use this option (only available in 2-column\n"
"layout) to show the cross-references at the end\n"
"of the 2nd column of text."
msgstr "Yu ken yusim dispela opesen (ol i wokim long 2-pela kolon tasol) bilong soim ol kru-referens long pinis bilong namba 2 kolon bilong teks."

#: temp.glade:23203
msgid "Placement of cross-references: End of page"
msgstr "Ples bilong ol kru: Ples daunbilo"

#: temp.glade:23207
msgid "Cross-references are usually placed \n"
"at the end of each page."
msgstr "Ol i save putim ol tok i kam long pinis bilong ol pes."

#: temp.glade:23229
msgid "Placement of Cross-References:"
msgstr "Ples bilong ol kruisen:"

#: temp.glade:23239 temp.glade:23240
msgid "Start Each Cross-Reference on a New Line"
msgstr "Kirapim ol nupela lain long ol narapela lain"

#: temp.glade:23244
msgid "Normally cross-references are arranged one after\n"
"the other to form a block of text. But if you \n"
"require each cross-reference to start on its own new\n"
"line then set this option."
msgstr "Ol i save putim ol kru-referens i go i kam bilong kamapim wanpela hap tok. Tasol sapos yu laik bai olgeta kru-referens i mas stat long nupela lain bilong en, orait putim dispela opsen."

#: temp.glade:23262
msgid "Override hidden/automatic Cross-reference caller settings"
msgstr "Override hidden/automatic Cross-reference caller settings (Raitim aut ol sait bilong ol man i ring)"

#: temp.glade:23263
msgid "Override Cross-Reference Settings in Text"
msgstr "Rausim Ol Karis Referens Insait Long Ol Tok"

#: temp.glade:23267
msgid "Cross-references specified in Paratext use\n"
"\\x +(plus) to cycle through the callers,\n"
"or \\x - (minus) to omit the caller.\n\n"
"If this option is enabled, the Show Callers\n"
"settings below will override whatever\n"
"has been specified within the text itself."
msgstr "Sapos yu larim dispela rot, ol senis long ol pes i stap daunbilo bai senisim ol tok yu bin raitim long ol pes."

#: temp.glade:23294
msgid "Show Cross-Reference Callers in the Text"
msgstr "Lukim ol lain i ringim long ol narapela hap bilong ol tok"

#: temp.glade:23299
msgid "A \"Caller\" is a symbol (in the text) which\n"
"alerts the reader that there is further\n"
"information (in this case a cross-reference\n"
"at the bottom of the page). Some people\n"
"prefer not to indicate cross-references in\n"
"the text itself, but just to include them at\n"
"the bottom of the page.\n\n"
"Separate callers with a comma (no spaces).\n"
"For example: a,b,c,d,e,f,g,h, etc.\n"
"or:  †,‡,§,∥,#    or: ✶,☆,✦,✪\n\n"
"If you do not see the callers you are \n"
"expecting in the PDF, then try using \n"
"the \"Override...\" setting above."
msgstr "Wanpela \"Caller\" em wanpela mak (long teks) we i toksave long man i ritim buk olsem i gat sampela moa infomesen (long dispela kain taim, wanpela kruis-referens long daunbilo bilong pes). Sampela man i no laik soim kruis-referens insait long teks yet, tasol ol i laik putim ol long daunbilo bilong pes. Ol i mas makim ol kruis-referens wantaim kom (no gat hap hap). Olsem: a,b,c,d,e,f,g,h, etc. o: †,‡,§,,# o: ,☆,, Sapos yu no lukim ol kruis-referens yu wetim long PDF, orait traim long yusim \"Override\"... saiting antap."

#: temp.glade:23328
msgid "Cross-Reference Caller Sequence Entry"
msgstr "Toktok long ol narapela narapela hap bilong ol man i ringim"

#: temp.glade:23352
msgid "Reload cross-reference callers from Paratext"
msgstr "Reload ol kru-referens kol bilong Paratext"

#: temp.glade:23356
msgid "Clicking this button will reload\n"
"the cross-ref callers from the\n"
"Paratext project settings.\n\n"
"If the callers have not been defined \n"
"in the Paratext project, or are already\n"
"showing, then a default set will appear."
msgstr "Sapos yu klik long dispela boton, dispela bai kirapim bek ol man i save ring long ol narapela hap long ol sait bilong Paratext projek. Sapos ol i no bin makim ol dispela man long Paratext projek, o ol i stap pinis, orait wanpela default set bai kamap."

#: temp.glade:23389
msgid "Show cross-reference callers in notes area"
msgstr "Lukim ol man i ringim long hap bilong ol not"

#: temp.glade:23394
msgid "Usually the \"Caller\" symbol is also shown\n"
"in the notes area which helps the reader \n"
"quickly find the cross-reference from the text."
msgstr "Planti taim ol i save putim piksa \"Caller\" long hap bilong ol not na dispela i helpim man i ritim na kwiktaim em i painim ol tok i stap long ol narapela hap."

#: temp.glade:23411
msgid "Reset cross-reference callers on each page"
msgstr "Resiet ol kalen bilong ol narapela pes"

#: temp.glade:23440
msgid "Click to edit the Cross-Reference properties on the Styles tab."
msgstr "Klik long senisim ol pasin bilong Cross-Reference long Styles tab."

#: temp.glade:23454
msgid "Below Footnotes"
msgstr "Ol Futnot"

#: temp.glade:23455
msgid "Placement of cross-references: Below footnotes"
msgstr "Ples bilong ol kru: aninit long ol tok daunbilo"

#: temp.glade:23459
msgid "Cross-references will be listed in a separate block\n"
"underneath the footnotes (rather than combined\n"
"along with the footnotes as a single paragraph)."
msgstr "Ol i mas raitim ol tok i stap long narapela hap aninit long ol tok i stap daunbilo (no olsem ol i mas bungim wantaim ol tok i stap daunbilo olsem wanpela paragraf)."

#: temp.glade:23477
msgid "Blend with Footnotes"
msgstr "Mekim Wankain Long Ol Futnot"

#: temp.glade:23478
msgid "Placement of cross-references: Blend with footnotes"
msgstr "Ol tok i stap long rot bilong ol kru: Blend wantaim ol tok daunbilo"

#: temp.glade:23482
msgid "To save space in the footnote area, you can\n"
"combine the  footnotes and cross-references\n"
"as a single paragraph (rather than the cross-\n"
"references appearing in a separate block\n"
"underneath the footnotes). If this option is\n"
"used, the Cross-References can only have\n"
"one type of caller (rather than a sequence)\n"
"which must be specified above."
msgstr "Bilong abrusim hap bilong ol tok i stap daunbilo, yu ken bungim ol tok i stap daunbilo na ol tok i stap long narapela hap bilong ol tok i stap daunbilo long wanpela paragraf (no olsem ol tok i stap daunbilo i mas stap long narapela blok.)"

#: temp.glade:23506 temp.glade:24405
msgid "Column Cross-References"
msgstr "Ol Kolon i Gat Ol Tok i Kam Long Ol"

#: temp.glade:23507
msgid "Placement of cross-references: Vertical column"
msgstr "Ples bilong ol kru: Long stik"

#: temp.glade:23512
msgid "When there are numerous cross-references (usually\n"
"when using an external list of references) then it\n"
"may be useful to place them in their own column. \n\n"
"The cross references will appear in a narrow vertical\n"
"column similar to a study/reference Bible layout."
msgstr "Taim i gat planti olpela tok i stap long Baibel (olsem taim yu yusim ol narapela buk o nius) orait i gutpela long putim ol dispela tok long kolon bilong ol yet."

#: temp.glade:23534 temp.glade:23535
msgid "Use External List of Cross-References"
msgstr "Yusim Ol Referens Bilong Yurop"

#: temp.glade:23539
msgid "Instead of using a handful of cross-references\n"
"as specified within the project's USFM text, you\n"
"can select an external list containing many 1000's\n"
"of cross-references. These will automatically be\n"
"localized into the project's language using the\n"
"\\toc3 values specified in the Paratext project\n"
"settings (See: Scripture reference settings...)\n\n"
"This feature is usually used for Study or\n"
"Reference Bibles in conjunction with the \n"
"'Column Cross-References' placement option."
msgstr "Yu no ken yusim sampela liklik ol tok i stap insait long ol tok bilong projek, nogat, yu ken makim wanpela lista i gat planti tausen tok i stap insait long en. Ol bai yusim ol tok i stap insait long tokples bilong projek long ol tokples ol i kolim long ol paratext project setting (Lukim: Scripture reference settings...)"

#: temp.glade:23563 temp.glade:23564
msgid "Show Extended Cross-References"
msgstr "Lukim Ol Tok i Stap Long Ol narapela hap"

#: temp.glade:23568
msgid "Study Bibles can (optionally) use extended\n"
"cross-references (\\ex) which can be displayed\n"
"along with other kinds of cross-references."
msgstr "Ol Baibel bilong stadi long en inap yusim ol tok i stap long ol narapela hap bilong Baibel (ol i no makim) na ol inap soim ol dispela tok wantaim ol narapela kain tok i stap long ol narapela hap."

#: temp.glade:23583
msgid "Include Cross-References (From Project Text)"
msgstr "Kisim Ol Referens (Long Ol Tok Bilong Projek)"

#: temp.glade:23584
msgid "Include cross-references (from project)"
msgstr "Toksave long ol narapela samting (long projek)"

#: temp.glade:23589
msgid "Select whether cross-references from\n"
"the project's text should be included.\n\n"
"The specific settings for these are\n"
"located on the Cross-References tab."
msgstr "Makim sapos yu laik putim ol kru-referens long ol tok bilong projek. Ol senis bilong ol dispela kru-referens i stap long tab Kru-referens."

#: temp.glade:23610
msgid "Only show verse numbers from \\xo"
msgstr "Lukim ol namba bilong ol ves long \\xo tasol"

#: temp.glade:23614
msgid "The cross-reference origin \\xo usually\n"
"includes the chapter & verse number\n"
"like this 3:16. If you prefer to hide the\n"
"chapter, so that only 16 is shown, then\n"
"enable this option."
msgstr "Ol tok piksa i stap long ol hap bilong Baibel i gat namba bilong sapta na ves olsem 16."

#: temp.glade:23676 temp.glade:23707
msgid "The various cross-reference lists often contain\n"
"hundreds of 1000s of references. You may want\n"
"to only include target references that are\n"
"currently available to your readers by \n"
"selecting a subset of Biblical books.\n\n"
"So for example, if there is no Old Testament \n"
"yet, you may want to only include target \n"
"cross-references to NT Books.\n\n"
"If you select Books in \"This Publication\", \n"
"then only cross-references targetting \n"
"books in the list of Multiple Books on \n"
"the Basic tab will be included."
msgstr "Sampela buk yu laik lukim long ol narapela buk i gat planti tok bilong en. Sapos yu laik lukim ol buk i stap long ol narapela buk, yu ken putim ol tok i stap long ol buk bilong Baibel. Sapos yu laik lukim ol buk i stap long ol narapela buk, yu ken putim ol tok i stap long ol narapela buk."

#: temp.glade:23691
msgid "Include Refs\n"
"for Books in:"
msgstr "Toksave long ol buk long:"

#: temp.glade:23702
msgid "Include references for which category of books"
msgstr "Toksave long wanem kain buk"

#: temp.glade:23740
msgid "External Refs:"
msgstr "Ol narapela lain:"

#: temp.glade:23750
msgid "Select external list of cross-references"
msgstr "Makim ol narapela lain i gat ol narapela kain tok"

#: temp.glade:23755
msgid "There are multiple options to choose\n"
"from if you wish to use an external list\n"
"of cross-references. Select whichever\n"
"is most appropriate and the list will\n"
"automatically be localized to use the\n"
"abbreviated book names as defined in\n"
"Paratext's Scripture Reference Settings\n"
"which should match the \\toc3 markers."
msgstr "Sapos yu laik yusim ol narapela buk yu ken makim ol nem bilong ol buk yu laik yusim. Sapos yu laik yusim ol narapela buk yu ken makim wanpela nem i stret long yu, na ol buk yu laik yusim bai i kamap long nem bilong buk yu laik yusim."

#: temp.glade:23781
msgid "Select a custom cross-reference list"
msgstr "Makim wanpela ol i bin wokim long ol yet"

#: temp.glade:23802
msgid "Standard"
msgstr "Ol lo"

#: temp.glade:23803
msgid "Source of cross-references: Standard list"
msgstr "Ol i yusim ol narapela rot bilong stori long ol samting"

#: temp.glade:23807
msgid "The Standard List contains more \n"
"than 340,000 cross-references\n"
"which have been prioritized by\n"
"crowd-sourcing."
msgstr "Dispela Standar List i gat ol 340,000 kruis-referens i stap, na ol i bin makim ol samting ol i laik mekim long rot bilong ol lain i gat planti wok long en."

#: temp.glade:23825
msgid "Strongs"
msgstr "Strongpela samting"

#: temp.glade:23826
msgid "Source of cross-references: Strong's list"
msgstr "Ol i yusim Strong's List"

#: temp.glade:23830
msgid "The Strong's List contains a curated\n"
"subset of cross-references generated\n"
"from the Strong's Numbers. Optionally\n"
"an index for these numbers can also\n"
"be created as an additional book that\n"
"can be appended to the publication.\n\n"
"Each set of cross-references is indexed\n"
"by a Hebrew or Greek Strong's number\n"
"which can be looked up in the (optional)\n"
"Index which can be generated using the\n"
"\"Generate Index...\" button."
msgstr "Strong's List i gat ol liklik lain kru-referens ol i bin wokim long Strong's Numbers. Ol inap wokim wanpela indeks bilong ol dispela namba olsem wanpela buk moa ol inap putim wantaim dispela buk. Ol i save wokim ol kru-referens long wanpela namba bilong Strong long tok Hibru o Grik."

#: temp.glade:23857
msgid "TSK"
msgstr "Ol tok bilong ol"

#: temp.glade:23858
msgid "Source of cross-references: Treasury of Scripture Knowledge"
msgstr "Ol tok bilong dispela buk i kam long: Treasury of Scriptural Knowledge"

#: temp.glade:23862
msgid "For generations, the Treasury of Scripture Knowledge\n"
"has been an enduring cross-reference resource for Bible\n"
"students worldwide. This highly respected and nearly\n"
"exhaustive compilation of cross-references was developed\n"
"by R.A. Torrey from references in the Rev. Thomas Scott's\n"
"Commentary and the Comprehensive Bible. With nearly\n"
"500,000 cross-references it is the most thorough source\n"
"available."
msgstr "Inap planti handet yia, Treasury of Scripture Knowledge i bin stap olsem wanpela gutpela rot bilong ol sumatin bilong Baibel long olgeta hap bilong graun long skelim ol tok bilong Baibel."

#: temp.glade:23886
msgid "BibWrx"
msgstr "Ol tok bilong Baibel"

#: temp.glade:23887 temp.glade:23911
msgid "Source of cross-references: The Works"
msgstr "Ol tok i kam long The Works"

#: temp.glade:23891
msgid "The BibleWorks list contains 112,000 cross-references\n"
"which were formerly part of the BibleWorks software\n"
"which has been discontinued."
msgstr "Long lista bilong ol program bilong BibleWorks, i gat 112,000 ol tok i stap long ol narapela program bilong BaibelWorks, em ol i no wokim moa."

#: temp.glade:23910
msgid "UBS"
msgstr "Ol lain bilong UBS"

#: temp.glade:23915
msgid "This list contains New Testament and Old Testament\n"
"references (NO Deuterocanonical  references). Short\n"
"Bible Reference System, edited by Robert G. Bratcher,\n"
"(c) 1961 United Bible Societies. This list was used in\n"
"GNT92. Organizations that have a Paratext license may\n"
"use this list in their publication without attribution or\n"
"notifying UBS. All other rights to use this list are reserved.\n\n"
"Use the (DC) list if Deutero Canonical references are needed."
msgstr "Dispela lista i gat ol tok bilong Nupela Testamen na Olpela Testamen (NO Deuterocanonical references). Short Bible Reference System, em Robert G. Bratcher, (c) 1961 United Bible Societies i bin redim. Dispela lista i bin yusim long GNT92. Ol oganaisesen i gat Paratext lisens ol inap yusim dispela lista long ol pablikesen bilong ol, na ol i no ken toksave long UBS. Olgeta narapela raits bilong yusim dispela lista i stap bilong ol yet."

#: temp.glade:23938
msgid "Source of cross-references: Custom .xrf list"
msgstr "Ol kru-referens i kam long: Custom .xrf list"

#: temp.glade:23942
msgid "You can select a specially-curated list of cross-references.\n"
"For example. it is possible to extract cross-references from\n"
"another project (in the .xrf file format) to be included here.\n"
"There is also an .xre format (extended .xrf) and an .xml\n"
"format which can be used as external cross-references.\n"
"These formats are explained in the documentation.\n"
"Search Google for \"ptx2pdf/xrefs.md\""
