#: temp.glade:30387 temp.glade:30422 temp.glade:30450
msgid "When the different texts of a diglot are merged, there are various \n"
"algorithms which may be used to obtain the best overall result:\n\n"
"* Document based - attempts to use the document structure to align at \n"
"  paragraphs as far as possible; but alignment is easily confused when \n"
"  each text has a very different paragraph structure.\n\n"
"* Chapter Verse - aligns on chapters and verses instead of structure\n\n"
"* Scored - an alternative algorithm using weighted scores which\n"
"  tries to align paragraphs when the verse numbers match\n\n"
"* Scored (Chapter) - as a minimum, forces alignment at chapters breaks \n\n"
"* Scored (Verses) - as a minimum, forces alignment at each verse, which \n"
"  can result in a lot of breaks!\n\n"
"Note that for polyglots, only the Scored options are available to be used."
msgstr "Taim ol i bungim ol narapela narapela tok bilong wanpela diglot, ol i gat sampela kain pasin bilong skelim ol tok bilong en bilong kisim gutpela samting: * Ol i yusim ol tok bilong wanpela dokiman - ol i traim long yusim ol tok bilong wanpela dokiman bilong stretim ol paragraf inap long skel bilong ol paragraf; tasol taim ol narapela tok i gat narapela narapela hap bilong ol paragraf, ol i no save stretim ol tok. * Chapta (Chapter) - i save bihainim ol sapta na ol ves na i no ol ves bilong en * Scored - wanpela narapela pasin bilong yusim ol score we i gat pe bilong en na i traim long bihainim ol paragraf taim namba bilong ol ves i stret * Scored (Chapter) - i no gat narapela rot long ol sapta i no kamap stret * Scored (Verses) - i no gat narapela rot long ol sapta i no kamap stret, olsem na planti hap bilong ol ves i no kamap stret!"

